hatever ... and over there we have the barrack we go to live in . why I mention the well , because I tell you what the well be . people they know already , not from the begin like from Warsaw they transport ... they start on the 22nd of July 1942 , so people they know already what Treblinka be .", "we find a piece ... a piece of bread . we find sometime a bottle of water which be a really ... some of they they bring in other thing to eat , but over there those people they work in Treblinka no. 2 , they have no chance . all they get be naked people go in and dead people take out from the gas chamber . Q : how long do you work as a barber in the gas chamber ? a : in the gas chamber we be work as a barber over there between 2 ... little more than 2 week .", "a : in the gas chamber we be work as a barber over there between 2 ... little more than 2 week . not for 3 week . and then they decide that the barber will not go in anymore to the gas chamber to cut off the hair of the woman over there , but in the undress barracks , they divide a part ... let 's say like you take here , divide a part and on this side they put the same thing . bench around and we cut the hair off , not in the gas chamber anymore . that be the last time ... the 3 ... the 2 or 3 week we work over there , we work .", "I myself for 4 month I do not see a woman with clothes . all I do be my job in the gas chamber . all these people be all naked without any clothing . first time I see a woman it be strange to I to see a woman . and she be so nice .", "we do also in that small ghetto organize like a little restaurant where people , you know , cooking , buy this that . what we do ... I have a brother-in-law , and this other gentleman by the name of Eisner , he have a brother-in-law also . and they be run around almost naked without anything . what we do ... we take out money and we say , `` here be a room . you buy all kind of food you can get .", "I do not want to go in . '' I say , `` if you be not go in , I be not go in either . '' what it happen , people go in and they with dynamite they destroy the whole land of that strip about 6 , 7 house . take out 3 , 4 ... 3 story , 4 story , 2 story and all the people get kill . the rest of the people the judenrat and most of the police they take to the cemetery and they kill they .", "they be put into a big machine or something like that , in a container and which supposedly be heat up so that it should kill these lice but they never be kill . they be only worse every time that when you get you clothes back . and meantime you go -- have to go to a shower bath and the ss -- male and female -- be , we be totally naked . we be stand around . they be stand there talk to one another , laugh they head off that we be all stand there in -- with nothing on helplessly .", "keep there , and soak wet , with very little to eat . what we bring , gather in that one hour which I mention when the police bang on we door . everything we be strip of . the only thing , as I mention , we be allow to be take the clothes which we have on , a blanket and some pot and pan . now from that place about three or four day later , when enough Jews be gather , we be put on horse-drawn cart and we be take into a brick factory nearby .", "a : when uh Mengele motion to I to the right , of course , I go immediately into the group where my father and my older brother be . because then they would be separate man and woman . and we be take to a building where we be strip from everything now , even what we have on we back . every ... everything we have to leave . and we be shaven , and everywhere where you can imagine .", "once they enter into that large room and the door be lock , they would let gas in there . now , what the terrible thing be in ... one of the ... one of the lucky thing , in a way , for I ... the terrible thing be they would be dead . of course , they would be stark naked . they would be send we to go and pick up the dead body who they just ga