 but there be nothing to cover up with . we be stark naked standing there . and we go through this dehumanizing ... uh ... process of be shave by all these man after which we be all give a clean dress . it be a grey ... like a man 's shirt , a grey shirt , but very long .", "the -lsb- sauna -rsb- be a place where ... where they ... they disinfect station ... be a disinfect station . whatever we have with we , it be ... what we be carry with we , they take away everything . we have to strip completely and they be internal ... they be check we out completely ... if we do not hide something . Yah ? gold or ... or jewelry or something like that .", "gold or ... or jewelry or something like that . and they take we in a very cold room . I be freezing , all naked , and there they be ... be a whole group of barber and they ... uh strip we hair completely . Yah . all over .", "that ... that be not heat . nothing ! we be all naked . after that they ... they bring we in a place where they give we these uniform . Yah ?", "after that they ... they bring we in a place where they give we these uniform . Yah ? the strip prisoner uniform . then we know what it be , and nothing else . all we ... clothing , civil clothing and everything be go .", "and then they take we in . they frisk we . they take my ... a matron take my mother and I in a room and tell we to strip and ... uh ... and ... uh ... the matron say to I , `` be not you afraid ? '' I say , `` no . '' -lrb- laughing -rrb- and then ... and then ... uh ... they ask to see we id , so my father produce we fake id and they say , `` who do you think you be kid .", "sometimes they take people out any time , anybody to do different kind of work . what they do , they cut the hair of the woman . the woman go to the gas chamber after the man and then they stop , about one or two barracks before the gas chamber be a barrack where they leave they luggage and they have to undress ; and there be a barrack the next to the gas chamber where they cut at randomly , they cut the hair of the woman . they utilize it . they send it back to Germany ; they do for brush , for everything .", "if the polish transport be -- the polish Jews know more what be go on . they know they be go to death and also they be more religious and the woman come in 3 Oberscharf\u00fchrer Gustav Wagner 4 Oberscharf\u00fchrer Hubert Gomerski and we be young boy , 20 , 22 , five , and we be stand there . 01:38:30 they come naked in , and we have to cut they hair . there be a horrible yell and scream for all these , from know , from feel they go to the gas chamber . on top of that , they be ashamed to put it in .", "when we arrive there , we smell the smoke . be dark . and when we get out from the wagon , we see people out the door strip dress ... uh , coat . they be polish people , mostly . they speak yiddish ; and they say , `` you have to do separate lane ... uh , line .", "and we see a big side light on the ... direct towards we , that ... and on there be stay a very nice look ss man . and we find out later that man be Mengele . and beside he there be some helper -- people with those strip coat ; and with the ... he hand he point to people . and because I be not on he side on the line -- I be the inside line -- he point to I , and come two man . they grab I and put I out from the line , on the right side .", "and some also very bad shoe ; and they put we immediately , still wet , outside in the ... in the yard . outside the wash building . and there , from far away , be the men also ; because we see people with those strip coat . and up today , I think -- and maybe be just imagine -- that I see my father between they . but I have ... I be not sure .", "but uh we very much afraid of lice . during the Auschwitz stage , I pass two time through a selection . there come doctor from uh ... I do not know from where , ss doctor ; and we ... we ... naked , we shoot past in front of they . and if somebody have some little uh sign on he ... on he uh body , this for put on the left . and they take they to the crematorium .", "and we be fight for a whole new world mean for everybody and for a larger number of Jews , and even if there be a few casualty there always be in war . and the last point I want to make with you gentleman be that they should remain here . if you come from Germany from the american commander to find out if the Jews here be go to flee , if I have anything to do I will see to it that they will leave this country nakt und barfuss , they will go out naked and barefoot because they should not go out . well , you know , this be zero for four . we have see four people , the Ambassador , the Prime Minister , the Cardinal , and then the communist leader , and you get no sympathy from any of they .", "well , some people run and they try to get people out of that jail . but nobody succeed . these thousand man be take out to a forest near we city by the name of Kuzhi , where they be make to dig they own grave , they be make to get undressed naked , they be shoot and they be cover with earth . how do we know exactly what happen there ? the farmer in the area .", "you know , she be take to another side which I be not too sure whether she be take to be kill or to another side of the camp . my group of woman from the age of 16 to 25 , we be take into a very large room , group by group , I do not know 200 or whatever , I really do not know exactly the count . we be tell to get completely undressed naked , the guard stand around and around . you know when I think of that moment I still remember how I do not know which part to hide . should I cover the top , should I cover the bottom .", "they say you have next to you dead , take it out . and then it be you know very cold and many people think gee , I will take that blanket or the dress of the dead and put it over I so I will keep warm . so many , many of these body be already naked . that be why you see sometime picture near the barracks that be naked because we figure , `` they be dead . they do not need that garment .", "and then it be you know very cold and many people think gee , I will take that blanket or the dress of the dead and put it over I so I will keep warm . so many , many of these body be already naked . that be why you see sometime picture near the barracks that be naked because we figure , `` they be dead . they do not need that garment . maybe I will save my life . ''", "it be hard for he to listen . and we have three lovely child , who be good human being . somehow we survivor , because we suffer , because we need , because be hungry , because be naked , implant in we child to be sensitive to those need . and most of they really grow up to be involve in help other human being . document and photograph -lrb- 1 -rrb- as I tell you , my aunt and my uncle , Mr. and Mrs. Jaffe , live in New York -- they come here in 1928 .", "the Poles in the community , the the gentile in the community be against we too . I be not go to say all of they . I would not be alive today if it be all of they , but a great number be and uh we part of the country be a very poor part of the country and I guess the the looting be what uh what appeal to a lot of the people , be able to uh to accumulate somebody ... you know , take over somebody else 's wealth and even though by the time we come into the ghetto a lot of it be strip , but it be still some thing . when you talk about a community where people do not even have shoe ... uh my husband still kid I about I come from a small town where you walk barefoot . you only put on you shoe when you come to the market place .", "a. . . a barrack or whatever you want to call it , open up and they tell we to undress . and , of course , you know , the ss be walk around there and there be so many girl that do not want to underess completely and they start beat on they and they have to get undressed . and then they start shave we head and ... uh ... I remember stay there and these ss walk around we and if the girl would put down they head , just try to , just try to hide , they would come up and they would take they whip and they would pull they head up like this with the whip and they would look at we and then they would start whipping we .", "little do I know that she have , she have poison that she carry with she and she keep it for the last minute , if necessary . I find that out when we get to Ravensbruek and we stay in line to go into the bath house and she ask I while we be stay in line if , if I think that , be it time or not yet ? and I say , `` oh , let 's wait and see , '' and by the time we get in and we be order to strip and give everything away , she do not have it anymore . 02:20:00 Q : could you tell I about the arrival in Ravensbruek , please ?", "I think I be first , and we get consecutive number and from then on we have no name , just number , and then we go to the bath house . we -- as I say they take away we clothes . 02:23:05 we have to strip . everybody be shave . I do not know by what miracle Pepi and I be not shave .", "usually they catch . they catch two of they and they take out the whole camp there one night and they be hang he publicly like everybody should see . they wake we up in the middle of the night and everybody come out naked almost and it be not even -- they tell they to take off . everybody be half naked outside and be February , I think -- the beginning of March cold . terribly .", "they catch two of they and they take out the whole camp there one night and they be hang he publicly like everybody should see . they wake we up in the middle of the night and everybody come out naked almost and it be not even -- they tell they to take off . everybody be half naked outside and be February , I think -- the beginning of March cold . terribly . and a lot of we get pneumonia .", "when I remind myself , I want to cry now . it be my job . people naked , half naked . Ladies ! men !", "you be go to get a shower and a uniform , and everything you possess if somebody have something from the 68 ghetto , whatever it be . there be a new german at a table and give it to they . you have to be completely undress when you go into the shower . we know . we hear about the story of the crematorium and this , but somehow we do not feel this a work camp and the guy say , do not worry .", "there be 5,000 people in this camp and maybe there be a couple thousand people . they call a transport in the train and they come from other place and put everything over there . we have to undress and we have to go into in this ______ . we have to wait but we do not know . we do not see people come out .", "my father be go but I can not . I be too young , but my father do not want to raise he hand to say he be not a doctor , but jewish people be a lot of intelligent people . but before the people , they tell they before they tell the people that have the uniform before they go to the back , undress I be go to give special 71 work for you . you be go to go inside and take out with you hand whatever you find this . you have to take out the waste from the people with they hand .", "once in a while they build a nice it be a barrack but it be better than the first one . and they have a little corridor and they be so ______ even in a work camp . they put in the people in the shower and most of they then we be all man and some man have a 83 desire , and they put a woman undress , completely naked and she would go and maneuver the water to make the water , to turn on the water . and there I be afraid . I be alive but some people be still in the man have a desire for a woman .", "I know the Germans be be be kill the Jews , but I do not know what they would do ... they have camp like this to ... you know , I do not . exterminate so many people ... I do not know . so I meet those people with the with the strip uniform and already they take off ... I do not know if they take because they take off they Juda -lrb- ph -rrb- ... you know , that ... so I give they a lot of food and they ... I give they clothes , and one day i go before uh uh ... I forget the name of the town ... before Auschwitz ... ... Q : do not worry about name of town ... a : no , no , no , no .", "question : before I ask you about the liberation , be there anything else , any particular story that you remember about the time that you live with the Janssens that you would like to to tell now ? answer : well , I can tell you something that tie right in to the day of liberation . one of the side element of the air war be a effort by the ally to disturb the german communication , and for a time they would drop lot of uh little strip of black paper with aluminum foil attach to they , which I guess uh disrupt radar and what happen I guess uh fly through a radar net that otherwise might detect plane that be come through , so we kid make a game of this . and we would go out in the field and hunt all those strip of paper and use they for art project . I still have a calendar for example that that where I make the backing out of out of those little bit of paper which we call silver paper .", "answer : well , I can tell you something that tie right in to the day of liberation . one of the side element of the air war be a effort by the ally to disturb the german communication , and for a time they would drop lot of uh little strip of black paper with aluminum foil attach to they , which I guess uh disrupt radar and what happen I guess uh fly through a radar net that otherwise might detect plane that be come through , so we kid make a game of this . and we would go out in the field and hunt all those strip of paper and use they for art project . I still have a calendar for example that that where I make the backing out of out of those little bit of paper which we call silver paper . and the area in which we be , atypical for the Netherlands , be solidly catholic .", "if you talk to they , they would respond . that be how I get the answer I do . one other thing be they mention that when they would beat these soldier -- or these prisoner -- or hang they up , they would strip they down nude . if you look at the body that you will see in these pile , you would see the black and blue mark of bruise on what be leave of the skin and so forth . and I mention about the expression .", "Q : where it be , what it be -- wait a minute . okay . a : this be a picture of a man , one of the prisoner , hold up a specimen bottle that have three strip of tattoo , the skin that be cut off the body of the prisoner that give they life for that practically . and these be the type thing that they would sew into the lamp that they be make as part of the lamp , the top part . there be many lamp make .", "do not volunteer that ... uh ... we be sick . '' we do not know what he mean , but ... uh ... so anyway all everybody come off the train and ... uh ... we have to leave everything on the train . naked . you know . they take over all the clothes , everything .", "you know . they take over all the clothes , everything . naked . and you stand in the line and mengele be sit there , Dr. Mengele they call he .", "you use to ... you put we to the , you know , throw we ... throw the people to ... uh ... the barb wire and ... and they get electrocute right there and die . and ... and crawl ... there be a man ... man ... uh ... in a man 's barracks and winter and it be cold . naked , they make he run around in the snow up to here , naked , and beat he up and same thing they do to the woman . -lrb- sigh -rrb- we be just there ... uh ... there for a long time and sit by the barb wire and every day , they ... they come in and they just beat we up , beat we up . they be ... they bring the food , you know , that little no-good food .", "a place that be ... you dig out potato and ... uh ... some start ... I do not know ... a lot of girl start ... uh ... go out there and ... uh ... they bring back some stuff to eat and what do you think ? they catch they . it be about 10 girl , and they catch they and they put they outside naked at night , and they ask everybody should come out and they take the machine gun and sound like this . that be it . then they take just anything girl .", "we walk in the camp in Maut ... to Mauthausen , a hundred people there . I think that be be the last transport , where they bring hungarian jewish people to Mauthausen , and we have see there , you know , when we get out and stand in line , we have see a lot of dead people where you come in to go in , they be already transfer from one place to another for week and week and week , and and then they choose some people to help uh take they to gather , to gather the clothes and what be leave over in the wagon , and I get one of the two uh choice -lrb- ph -rrb- , and I help just clean up the the wagon and then we put everything in such a a what people in the two wheel like wagon but we ... they ... instead horse , we pull it into the lager and the camp close with the what you have bringe back from from Hungary where they take they in the wagon , and then when I arrive in Mauthausen , when I arrive in Mauthausen ... I do not remember exactly the time ... I have see and we look in in in the lager , I have see in one side woman and one side man . and everybody be naked and then they cut we of the hair and they leave ... they leave a line in the head , they leave a line in the head ... be like to be recognize , you know . we be prisoner . uh we be con ... uh you know , camp people .", "uh tell I when you arrive into the camp , where be you take and what do you do ? a : I be take , we be take to a block , I do not know exactly where . we then be ask to undress completely . naked . I have some photograph of my family which be tear to shred .", "a : I be take , we be take to a block , I do not know exactly where . we then be ask to undress completely . naked . I have some photograph of my family which be tear to shred . hair be 