o a cake of soap , hope , you know ; she push in a , in cake of soap , and she hope that this will somehow help we in the in the long run , because everything else be take away from we . but be the worst be that they have , that we have to undress and be search . they , they , they search -- they poke with , with a stick they poke in , in the vagina to see whether , whether people do not , be not hide anything . and my , my mother be a religious lady ; and , and first , that hurt I mostly , that she have to go through such , such a terrible ordeal .", "because she know , she know that my sister will suffer when she will find out where she take she grandson . and then I have a double challenge to keep my sister alive , because my sister eventually -- we -- there be not too long before we find out the truth -- where we be , and what be happen . because when they , they take we to a big room where we have to , where we have to undress and there be , and they take everything away from we . and just on the other side be the same big room , only that it have gas -- only gas be come out . this be where my mother and all the other be , in that gas chamber .", "and just on the other side be the same big room , only that it have gas -- only gas be come out . this be where my mother and all the other be , in that gas chamber . and we , be in another place that we have to undress and dress and they take everything away from we . and they shove we in to , to the shower , that we have to -- but what they do be , they first open the hot water so we get scald and then they open the cold water ; so as we , be run out , we , we , be we , be beat with the , with the whip to go under it . and then when we come out we , be all so -- and first they shave we .", "because if , if we would have be sel -- to be select , they would select we to the gas chamber because we , be already not in very good shape . so one , one day , they take we to those you know , to , to have we clothes disinfect . so they take , they take we to , to disinfect the clothes , and so we have to undress naked and wait for we clothes to be disinfect . and the ss be wait there with we , you know , with the dog . we , be surround by ss and the dog .", "you see I work with this ... this firm , schallhorn.and they be do the bridge you know and the planning you know from the ... and then in ' 40 ... 1943 , they make concentration camp . 'til ' 43 , it be the work camp . and then they come in one day , everybody have to strip they clothes . it be the winter , January . about two or three foot snow , frost .", "they take we in one barrack . take off all the clothes . we have to run to the other barracks , naked in this snow and freezing cold . and they give we they stripey uniform . I be sure you have hear from they , uniform what we be wear .", "and then we be put into separate room and we be ... I do not know what happen exactly to my mother and my brother . I know they be beat . I know I be strip completely and a little ... little beaten . and ... uh ... then I be ... we be release and we be think now we be on we way to Dachau . and I can not explain it but somehow they give we a opportunity to escape and we run and we escape .", "the next day they be carry out in one coffin ... one coffin , and there be a a team -lrb- ph -rrb- which do not do anything else but the whole day they they they carry the dead people out and uh and as I say , by November I guess one third of the people have die , and new people come in . uh at this time , before this happen , I be once order to go by truck to the station ... now I do not know whether whether Lauerhutte have a station or whether it be , to a station and I be sit with another buddy , with another inmate , next to the driver and in the back there be perhaps thirty or forty uh concentration camp inmate uh who have be all sick . they come from the sick bay , and when we come to the station , they have to undress naked and be push into a freight car and the reason why I and my buddy have to come along because we have to take they clothes and bring it back and they probably go to to Auschwitz to the gas , you know . we be in AuscHwitz and they go to the gas chamber . I do not know at what time we start to realize that there be gas chamber , but we do not understand this ... we identify gas chamber with crematoria and I think since we be people from ... come from the west , the knowledge of what really happen be give to we by Jews from Poland and from the I remember there be a group of Jews from , and they know what happen , but they could not explain it either .", "frankly , nobody know about gas ... I mean now it seem strange not to know about it , but I do not think we understand it . we know about crematoria and you know , you do not follow ... develop you idea since we know what happen ... how the person kill in the crematorium ... if he burn . we do not follow the ... the crematoria , that be the place where people be kill , and we do not go further and this incident which I tell you about with people be send naked , that be clearly a case , a instance where people be send to death , but I must say it take a long time until I and I think all the other start to realize that we be condemn to dea ... to die and all pe ... all Jews be condemn to die . for some time we believe the Germans be crazy and just kill people but that everybody be to be kill , that we do not understand . now on a personal note , around this time I once come in front of a mirror , and I see what be call a mussulman .", "and they have to take everything off , everything off . everything . naked . they tell they you go in a shower room , to take a shower . you get disinfection .", "you can not believe . we see this . I be so mad when I see the people naked go on on this place to the to the to _ that camp . it be day when we come at night we could not eat . in the six week I say .", "there be thousand of prisoner come out of ... uh come into and out of the camp . so uh when they finally process we , they do not give anything to wear . we be naked , and we be only wrap in a. . . in a blanket ; and this way I live several week .", "I could have be , you know , catch many many time , you know . I do not , so maybe because ... -rsb- -lsb- nb : text in precede bracket do not appear on videotape . -rsb- photograph id photo strip -- 3 photo of prisoner in striped uniform with shave head , resemble police mug shot . leave hand photo label : `` no. 564 , KL Auschwitz . '' Photograph of six person seat around a table , circa 1942 .", "then they take I to this , to the great prison cell that be about twenty , thirty prisoner , and they tell I they they have some of they also have similar experience . and the next morning , we come for a doctor ; yes , we should be check up , and how we be healthy and so . and so we stand naked , and the nurse , which be a prisoner doctor , look at I , and he tell I , look , you have here something , hernia , you know what be . but I have it never , so I do not know what it be . and he touch it here and it take uh pain .", "so he tell something to the ss man . maybe he will give it to he , and it be O.K. and so it be . and now we be strip naked , I will remember how it be in the prisoner . this be my experience . and then , we have some , in Hamburg we could have get in one month about twenty marc , yes , from how much from friend .", "in the death sector I will explain . and they make from these two farm house gas chamber , yes . two barracck where the people take off they belongings and then they be pull to these gas chamber naked and they be poison there , yes , and from this they be pull out by ______ commander and put in the grave , in the uh , mass grave . -lrb- yes -rrb- . yes , in the mass grave .", "but I do not know , as I say , whether she be instrumental in have we neighbor murder or she boyfriend of whatever , but I remember my mother tell we not to talk loud and not to say thing so much so because it be none of that woman 's business , and I understand now why . at any rate uh the woman and she boyfriend take a trip to Paris in the year uh 1943 and uh they return on the first evening of Rosh HaShanah at which time live in we house in we flat while she be go be a family of four people ... a man , he wife and the two child , and that be the man whom I have find with my mother the day when my father disappear . that friend , he and he wife and he two child who have be pick up by the Gestapo and whom my mother have help to liberate , somehow spring from they initial confinement and who have no place to go ... one of the thing that happen when the Gestapo take you be that they also come in and strip the house and take all you effect and uh so they have no place to live and they come and stay with we . after all the woman be not there and she boyfriend and I do not think anyone know they be come back and so ... but they ... it be right ... I remember it be Rosh HaShanah evening and the woman and she boyfriend come back and they have be in Paris and they bring we a gift and I remember the gift that my brother get be a little wind-up car that would not fall off the edge of the table when it , you know , they be common now but we would never see anything like that , so anyway uh we go to bed that night . I do not know how my mother must have feel .", "it must have be a factory and they tell we to get undressed . and they would make you take off the jewelry and everything , any valuable that you have on you . they undress -- they tell we to get undressed . we all do . the woman remain with the underwear only , and the man in they shorts .", "the sun be shine . the sky be blue . and so many people stand naked in that line wait to be kill . and my mother be look around and she see this tall Gestapo man . very , very tall .", "part of you life you lose . it be just a lot of anger . anger to the world for do such thing , and not to feel when all of we have to stand naked -- such inhumanity . we be just make to feel like animal . and the beating that one constantly have to go through there , all the people .", "in those day there be no more tire that have air in they . so we make tire out of old car tire . we cut strip of old car tire . but , of course , this be solid . it be like drive on wood you know .", "you could not even stand . you be just press like sardine . so the bread and the marmalade when the people have it in they hand , it be still in they hand because when they get to destination in Treblinka , they have to undress and they have to leave everything . so the same bread and the same marmalade come back for the new transport . and this go on constantly .", "there be snow and they drag we out and put we to the track in the middle of the night to clean ... clean the snow from the track . and then they ... we have a little jewish hospital where we use to go there . so they use to take ... some pick up ... some most beautiful lady , they pick they up , bring they to the hospital there , rape they and undress they and make fool out of they , and then they release they . that be fine . that be no ... not as bad then .", "`` at the end of we runway be the biggest God dam barrel -lrb- you will have to censor that -rrb- I have see and it stink . '' `` I will be right down . '' -lrb- laughter -rrb- I put my trailer on my jeep , and I go to the air strip and we unloaded what be a enormous barrel . you think of a barrel as this big . it be three time that big .", "it be beautiful . many many year ago of course ... pardon I ... I get a job in the beginning . first I work in a motel on Sunset Strip for a while and then uh my brother have a good friend here and he have a shop with optical instrument and I get a job there and I work there for a few year work for he and settle down and my wife then have a job also . she work uh on the Sunset Strip also in a knit shop . she be uh handwork ... she inherit from she ... she father be a great tailor and Marsha inherit that obviously from she dad and she be great with she hand .", "many many year ago of course ... pardon I ... I get a job in the beginning . first I work in a motel on Sunset Strip for a while and then uh my brother have a good friend here and he have a shop with optical instrument and I get a job there and I work there for a few year work for he and settle down and my wife then have a job also . she work uh on the Sunset Strip also in a knit shop . she be uh handwork ... she inherit from she ... she father be a great tailor and Marsha inherit that obviously from she dad and she be great with she hand . she be uh ... those time , those day I mean they be embroider sweater , you know , in mode and then she be work for this girl Suzie , name Suzie , on the Strip .", "she work uh on the Sunset Strip also in a knit shop . she be uh handwork ... she inherit from she ... she father be a great tailor and Marsha inherit that obviously from she dad and she be great with she hand . she be uh ... those time , those day I mean they be embroider sweater , you know , in mode and then she be work for this girl Suzie , name Suzie , on the Strip . she have a famous shop and she work for they . she meet a lot of movie star there too .", "the officer have everything and what I do be , they ... I say I want you to get those guy drunk , as drunk as you can . I have six russian soldier , seven because we can only get seven wait on the side ... I know approximately the size of the officer because they come to visit very often , and they send I seven of they ... I get they so drunk they could not move . we undress they . we put the polish uniform on the russian soldier . they take , they steal six horse .", "and I meet a family friend there , which probably be my best -- that be probably my most important moment to survive . there be a couple of other , but when we leave the Umschlagplatz where we get out of the boxcar we be take into a barracks . I remember we be stark naked . men only . and they be tattoo we .", "now what they do ... I be a fugitive so they put I in the attic . I remember the attic be like a thin attic . it be about maybe five foot high and it be so hot and I be completely strip naked and I be just fainting and sometimes I take a rag in my own urine and I put it over my head to cool off . it be unbearable and they ... they must have be fear for they safety and they come up . they say you have to leave because we be afraid to keep you here any longer , so I get dress and I put my arm band and I go ... take the streetcar to my hometown where my brother be lay there .", "of course I get hit . what they do , they dehumanize you . what they do they keep you stark naked without any service or without any food . I do not know whether it be twenty-four hour or forty-eight hour ... I can not tell , but at that time we get dehumanize by stand naked without any facility , without any food , wall to wall . I remember that because that be a quite a quite a bad experience .", "what they do , they dehumanize you . what they do they keep you stark naked without any service or without any food . I do not know whether it be twenty-four hour or forty-eight hour ... I can not tell , but at that time we get dehumanize by stand naked without any facility , without any food , wall to wall . I remember that because that be a quite a quite a bad experience . that be just ... prison camp name be Blechhammer .", "01:50 : Auschwitz . the ss come in . we all get strip naked and we all get tattoo . completely naked . men , woman separate of course .", "the ss come in . we all get strip naked and we all get tattoo . completely naked . men , woman separate of course . the be tattoo ... it be not the pain .", "that be a. . . quite a shock for all of we , especially ... we have the woman 's camp and the man 's camp separate , and I understand there be much more of a shock for for young woman stand in front of the ss completely strip naked . after ... well , after we build the factory I stay with that for quite a while and I say well , then I I count some some german who who be send from the factory to run the the building of the of this factory and certain specification and I remember I be sit in the corner and I be at that time welding pipe . I would ... the the master would ... call he master ... he be overhead .", "next night go thirty of we and load potato , sneak out one by one , so the Germans notice that the heap get to be smaller , so one night I open the door and they plant ss and they catch I . I get beat on the ... by the ss Wacht Stube , then come into the camp on the big appell . I get on my naked behind beaten twenty-five with the bullwhip . the first three , the man hit you as hard as a man can hit you . the first three whip ... that be all you feel .", "to a certain extent you be just like punchy . you do not care and you ... you be just not a human being . you be strip from everything and it be just ... you be not think much more than just ... you you have a pain in you stomach and you be cold . I remember lay and dream if I would ever be a free man , all I want to have be a hot glass of tea with a big loaf of bread , cut very thick slice , and I would just drink the hot tea and eat the bread , one by one . that be my biggest dream .", "there be hanging daily , and I could smell the burned flesh . they have ... when you get up in the morning , you go to the wash barracks . they would take all the corpse , un ... undress they and they be lay down like a collection in the wash barrack and they would take the number here , tattoo it big letter across the chest so they can check they out . when you get up in the morning , you go to the wash barrack , you step over some corpse and you wash you face and they have like a big row , just one faucet and a urn like to wash , and because the crematoria be too small , they would ... down the hill they would burn it completely , and the stench of burn flesh be always in the air . you would smell it completely .", "bei laufen . next day the Americans come into town and the farmer take I back in and they bring I to the Americans . now , anybody who do not live through be eat alive by lice will not understand that but when I come to the American , they undress I and they throw DDT and like the whole world stand still . I must go back , because when I come to the farmer , they take my ... my striped jacket out ... off , and they give I some ... some of they civilian clothes and they bury it ' it _ be so infested with lice , but I remember when they put I back I on the wagon to carry I to the Americans , I take like a visual picture of the farm because when I be lib ... liberate later on I come back and i. . .", "the only time we get the louse be at Dachau . they take away all we civilian clothes we have . they give we strip clothes because in Landsberg we be still in civilian clothes . they take some of the kid . they put I in the front soldier .", "we walk from Auschwitz to Birkenau . we do not go on train , we walk to there . that be in the evening , and they say everybody to undress you be go in for shower . they give you soap and they give you towel . the first group go in before we and we be next to go in and we be go into the crematorium .", "I never search they . one Sunday morning they have a inspection and they come in and they find potato in the box and vegetable . what happen , they get everybody out that be in November , we get everybody out completely naked undressed . he make they crawl on the ground like snake the whole day and the whole night . he come over to I and he take out he gun and I think he be go to kill I already .", "and uh the picture of a selection . have go through that uh once in you lifetime and you will never forget it . uh the uh infamous uh Dr. Mengele , he would stand at the head of the uh column of the procession of uh naked people and uh some way before reach , uh come up in front of Mengele , we see that uh there be left and there be right and uh what he be do be he would uh people would march up in front of he and uh he would look at they and whether they be still able body or not , able to contribute uh toward the work , to the labor in the factory . so uh when my turn come , and somebody be whisper to I uh to the right , and somehow I uh manage to stay in that right lane without be uh motion back to the left lane . that be what uh make the difference of life and death .", "the truck just take off and they uh they beat she down to the ground , my mother and uh could do nothing and uh I can imagine uh after the war for all these year to have to live with such memory , what it mean to uh to or to my father for that matter , that he could not uh that he could not protect my brother and that the uh guilt feeling , uh he feel that uh he have uh take my brother with he rather than have send he with I uh and that in turn may make he feel guilty if uh if I be able to survive and uh if he have let my older brother go together with I that he maybe he would have survive too . but that be the decision at that time , that uh he though he would be able to jump the train . -lrb- pause -rrb- up to uh up to a certain point yes , uh my parent be able to uh when they still have uh they have money and uh where they connection be able to uh do something for they , but when you reach uh Auschwitz , we be strip uh of we belongings and uh reduce to uh to object that they could do with uh whatever they want . -lrb- pause -rrb- you ask yourself uh how be it possible and uh -lrb- pause -rrb- to this day when I uh after have uh read and try to understand uh that whole episode of human history , how be it possible in the 20th century for a thing like this to happen and uh there be contradictory feeling and uh -lrb- pause -rrb- to try to explain rationally - there be no explanation . to try to say that uh -lrb- pause -rrb- once the people be tell uh that this be the policy of the government and uh therefore the lower echelon would accept it and go and follow through .", "they take the last hundred and take they away to be kill . and it take we ... he save we life and that ... this be a scene I will never forget . and they ... they take the people on the ninth fort ... they be ... they put in bunker and hear at that time tell ... they strip until the underwear and they walk out a hundred at a time they be machine gun for 3 day and then they cover they up with dirt . for 3 day the grave be move up and down . they take tractor and run over the grave in order to squeeze out the last breath .", "and we hug . the last time I ever see she . they take at night to the ... all the man ... they take we to the ... unclothe ... they take we to the ... uh ... the place where they keep we all night long , all naked . take all the clothes off , and we have to go in a. . .", "I think it be the end of of we all then . I be fifteen year old , and I be all alone in this hell . 01:30:36 they tell we when we come in , they tell we to undress and that we be go to be shower and that they be go to give we clothes . the place be so cold . it ... it ... it be in early winter ; and um it ... in Birkenau , this ... which be Poland , it be freezing cold .", "I feel like I be not a human person anymore . they have shave we head ; and I feel so ashamed . and also when they tell we to undress and to shower , they make we feel like ... like we be animal . the man be walk around , and laughing and look at we . and you take a young girl at that age , who be never be expose to um a person ... to a man , and you stay there naked ... I want the ground should open , -lrb- cry -rrb- and I should go in it .", "and also when they tell we to undress and to shower , they make we feel like ... like we be animal . the man be walk around , and laughing and look at we . and you take a young girl at that age , who be never be expose to um a person ... to a man , and you stay there naked ... I want the ground should open , -lrb- cry -rrb- and I should go in it . -lrb- pause - cry -rrb- it take I many many year for I to get over this . my husband always wonder why I would go into the bathroom and get undressed , and come out in my nightgown .", "and I never tell he why , except recently . it take all these year to tell he why . because I could never see anybody stare at I while I be naked . and I think that be what it be . because it be a just ... it be just terrible for I , what we have to go through at that age .", "we do not know that this will happen , but this be what it be . the jew ... the and the Jews be down ... be take down to the Danube River . the Danube river be frozen maybe ... I do not know how many inch thick , but they ... they throw some ... uh ... material , some military bomb or something into the water , probe the ... uh ... the thing open ... ice , the ice open and take the people into a place where they have to undress and naked to go on the trampoline which be over the Danube River , and they be shoot into the river . they be shoot and fall into the river . now , this go on for a long time .", "all of they be whip . and they tell we right away to line up and to get undressed . naked ! you know , one , you be only a person as soon ... as long as you have you clothes on . you can be a professor .", "you can be a scientist . you can be a shoemaker . but as long ... as soon as you clothes come up and you stand naked , you be lose . you be not a humanbee anymore . this be what I can not ... what I can not forgive the german that they ... they take off we ... systematically take ... take away we dignity .", "you be not a humanbee anymore . this be what I can not ... what I can not forgive the german that they ... they take off we ... systematically take ... take away we dignity . but undress we , many of the girl be young girl . they be virgin . they never see they parent naked , never see they mother naked , but all of a sudden we ... we have to go and get undressed .", "but undress we , many of the girl be young girl . they be virgin . they never see they parent naked , never see they mother naked , but all of a sudden we ... we have to go and get undressed . we be take to ... to the ... to someplace . they say that they be take out we to bath , to a general bath , a general bath .", "we be suffer of that dirt . everything be lice be crawl about people on the street . you could have see not ... not with the naked eye . you could have see more lice on the people than you could have see the clawing . all this be in preparation to give we a slow death .", "uh ... later on , later on I find out ... uh ... that ... uh ... you know , when you begin to question why and that be so we would not have we period . and ... uh ... that be another story beside that . so anyways , this be ... uh ... and then they give we a strip dress and clog , ... uh ... wooden clog . and ... uh ... then they give we a rusty tin can that look like full of rust for we food and they say that be ... we have to hold on because we life depend on that , but if we lose that we would get nothing . and ... uh ... then we be assign a barrack , and there be no room .", "the Nazis try to stop -- they try to interfere and cause static so they make we weave . we be tell that what it be -- I be not a hundred percent sure . they make we weave plastic -- braid plastic strip and they be go to drop this , hope that that would interfere with the radar transmission . they be drop this from plane and we be force to keep plait these thing in the Weberei . this be one of the job in the Weberei and we work there for a while .", "right , the belt . while I -- while we be in -- work in Kanada we be not allow to wear what be really -- would be consider civilian clothes . while , the people in camp , in the camp , be not give these strip clothes , not all of they , they be wear strip clothes . they be give the old rag clothes that be take off the body , and give to they and they last until they really fall off and they be full of mud and filth and lice . and then every so often they , they would -- the lice -- the clothes be take away and they be put in the gas chamber to kill the lice , and then of course all the nit be dead but they be all sit in the seam and be still there .", "a : oh gosh , the shoe . everyone be give shoe in regulation , these clog . they be just , you know , wooden sole and little canvas strip to hold , to put the foot in . the earth in Auschwitz be very muddy . it have be I understand no man 's land between the war and there be fish hatchery and it be very wet and humid .", "there be a big sink where we wash ourselves and then you can go toilet there and there be a guy and he have those high boot . a guy ... he be just a short for one week . he have 01:48 : those high , high boot and then Walter look at those boot and he say my gosh , I know ... I be shoemaker ... I know this ... in those boot , you know , there be strip of metal , of good steel . he say maybe we can make a saw out of this . so Walter go and talk to he ... how long you be here .", "and Gross Rosen be a camp , I at least do not see any bed . it be a transit camp of five day be the most that they would let you stay in that camp . they complete undress you . you could not have nothing that belong to you . they make you spread you you leg and and check , cut off you hair .", "uh I get permission , a pass , to visit the crematorium and into the camp . I be amaze . in contrast to the Waldenburg group , all I see be live skeleton -- gaunt people , many of they completely naked . uh many of they , you could not tell whether they be walk dead or walk alive . they face be expressionless .", "nothing there , no '' blanket or nothing . some of they sleep on the ... on the brick . then about 4:00 in the morning , we have to get up and stand naked even in the winter to see if we have a clear skin . there they count we in 5 , a hundred in a group , and the ss with the dog take we to work . we have to walk , let 's say , maybe 10 mile a day to work .", "well , they beat they up in the office . I have a girl what she be a secretary there and she tell they this . stripped they naked , and they beat they up with that ... how do you call it ? uh ... Q : A whip ?", "some do . some can not . people stand by ... by every day in Auschwitz , you have to go up 4 o'clock in the morning , stand in the line , shiver cold , strip until naked . that be to look for a little thing on the skin . which we do not have even water or anything for 7 month .", "we want to work . why do you do to we ? '' Start to beat they up and stand naked and nothing ... nothing then . how ... how can you fight back ? so they push they in the crematorium with the family .", "how do you get from England to Paris ? what be the circumstance ? answer : well , from England to Paris , uh I be uh fly over in a small plane together with a number of other officer , and we land on a air strip in Normandy . the uh german troops and uh I tell you be not that far away , and indeed as we plane land on the air strip in Normandy uh Ger ... german artillery begin shell the air strip . we be ask to uh leave the plane as quickly as possible and to run for cover , and uh of course I follow order very quickly .", "what be the circumstance ? answer : well , from England to Paris , uh I be uh fly over in a small plane together with a number of other officer , and we land on a air strip in Normandy . the uh german troops and uh I tell you be not that far away , and indeed as we plane land on the air strip in Normandy uh Ger ... german artillery begin shell the air strip . we be ask to uh leave the plane as quickly as possible and to run for cover , and uh of course I follow order very quickly . and uh in the process I lose a brand new officer 's trench coat that I have just purchase in London before departure for France .", "that be to say we cross the pass . my parent , not everyone but at random , people be take out of the plane ... out of the train and uh some of they be even uh bodily examine . now my mother be take into one room and my father in another , totally strip and totally examine and my mother can -- and I be leave with the Meyers on the train . for some reason the Meyers be not examine . as I say , people be take at random .", "uh but the situation become such that uh they would come eight or ten time a day to bomb . I mean you could not go to bed . you could not undress . there be week we would not undress because in the middle of the night you would have to run several time . uh it become such that you could not dare uh undress yourself to even wash yourself in the basin in you room because they would come to bomb .", "I mean you could not go to bed . you could not undress . there be week we would not undress because in the middle of the night you would have to run several time . uh it become such that you could not dare uh undress yourself to even wash yourself in the basin in you room because they would come to bomb . uh one day a high italian official come to the city and my mother , not be bashful , approach he in the parade and say it be impossible for we to remain here .", "you could not undress . there be week we would not undress because in the middle of the night you would have to run several time . uh it become such that you could not dare uh undress yourself to even wash yourself in the basin in you room because they would come to bomb . uh one day a high italian official come to the city and my mother , not be bashful , approach he in the parade and say it be impossible for we to remain here . I have a little child , and uh could we get permission , because here we be send here by the italian govern force , uh could I get permission to go to the next town , and the next town be call , also small town .", "they give we shower over there . of course , they cut we hair . Cut everything , you know , undress completely , cut everything . go under the shower and then they give we a new number because the Auschwitz number , the tattoo number be no good for Buchenwald . so , they give we a new number , and we have to go by the number now because nobody have a name .", "only the other people be the same way , they do to the other people the same thing . we be hide . I see on the way the supply landing strip , with truck , with food burning . we be run to the truck to see if maybe there be some kind of a food leftover , which do not burn . when you run to the truck , the Germans kill you .", "that the transport come . they kill the people . you see they run naked . and then you ... you sort out they belongings . but there be other thing that happen every day .", "and that building with the chalk kind of interested I because sometimes I would hear scream and I would see german soldier take woman there , woman that be maybe at that time maybe in they twenty or maybe older . they be develop a lot better . they be pretty woman and apparently they make some medical experiment , because through one window we peek and we see some man naked in big tub . they be metal tub , with ice and they would freeze they to a certain temperature and they would let the woman undress and I guess they want to see the sexual reaction and this be horrible to watch and pretty soon it be the turn for we . -lrb- pause -rrb- -lrb- cry -rrb- this be when you .", "they be develop a lot better . they be pretty woman and apparently they make some medical experiment , because through one window we peek and we see some man naked in big tub . they be metal tub , with ice and they would freeze they to a certain temperature and they would let the woman undress and I guess they want to see the sexual reaction and this be horrible to watch and pretty soon it be the turn for we . -lrb- pause -rrb- -lrb- cry -rrb- this be when you . -lrb- pause -rrb- and if you do not do what they want you to do , you will be beat up something terrible , or you be put under cold shower .", "a few break out into the open , only to be meet by a hail of rifle fire which cut they down , they clothing still burn . the smaller number that escape have clear they way through thick roll of barb wire , tear they burning flesh in a miraculous dash to safety . the rest be shoot down and they naked char body be still there when we troops arrive . so here on the outskirts of one of Germany 's greatest city , world famous for its beautiful building , its culture , its monument to great man , '' Leipzig , that be , `` there stand a monument to a new type of german culture that the world should never forget . `` and this be write in June of 1945 .", "water we find once in a while in the forest in the little stream . we find ... it be cold . we be almost naked . no clothes . and we find blueberry , frozen blueberry .", "it so happen that they point out one of my friend . a beautiful girl . she name be Susza Fein , and they put she and they undress she and they start to look in every place if she do not conceal something . she be in this time 19 year old . and they do it so cruel that they use instrument that they cut open she belly .", "and this be a emergency door . when he run out I shoot after he , and I hit he in the spine , and he fall down . now we be naked . my brother do not know what be go on . so he start to yell to they , `` what you play with firecracker ?", "and so , more or less I figure out that I will go this way and there be a house that I know this house , and this peasant be friendly . I say , `` if we would be lucky , and if I would hit this house , we would be save . '' now imagine if peasant will see we in the middle of the winter , two people naked without shoe . well , anyway , we start to go down , so I have my two revolver . I have everything on I .", "and so we we be march under guard every day to that to that factory , about uh five mile or maybe five kilometer from the ghetto in separate group and we work . the work be hard and miserable but we work and we come back and we meet at night in the ghetto and uh hope to hear something from we parent because we believe , or at least I believe ... I have no reason not to ... that they be someplace in the Ukraine . and of course that be ... there be no suspense then and of course they all go to a destruction camp and all the people be drive naked into gas chamber and kill . after about three week of work in that factory , one day ... and we group be maybe a group of hundred people ... after about three week of work and the march every day to that factory , one day when the work , when the job be over , the official in that factory say to we you be not go back . we have build a camp uh within the factory , right outside the factory wall but kind of adjoining the factory and you be stay here tonight .", "you have to remember a bowl of watery soup with some leaf or some piece of potato in it for two people who each one of they equip with he own spoon and and this be ready make for conflict and combat and and and and uh the the spilling of soup and so on , but somehow before I arrive a a custom be develop over there where the two prisoner , skeleton-looking hungary prisoner who would be give this bowl of soup to share , would feed each other , so if you give I half a spoon , I give you half a spoon . and if you dip down and find a piece of potato , I will dip down and give you a piece of potato , and so that custom or that habit or that arrangement which have both philosophical and not religious undertone , people manage to people who be stranger , people who be die of hunger manage somehow to be discipline and to go through that daily ritual of share the bowl of soup . after six week of work and hard labor ... oh yes ... I be I be forget something ... when we first come to Flossenburg , we be march by this young ss guard with they dog up the hill to the camp , we we be bring before a very large building in a kind of assembly area , and we be ... there be four hundred and fifty of we approximately , and we be all tell to undress , to leave we clothing on the floor and all we possession and we go in to take shower . now there be concern . there be speculation , because by that time we know about gas chamber .", "we know that we parent who be who go to the to the allegedly be send to that farm in the east be really kill and send to gas chamber . we know about that , and there be great concern that we may be take to a gas chamber . this be typical ... this the thing ... undress ... go in naked . but there be really no choice . the choice be to resist and be kill , to run , to fight , to or to just hope and to do what one be tell and hope that it be true that what they say that we will take a shower .", "the choice be to resist and be kill , to run , to fight , to or to just hope and to do what one be tell and hope that it be true that what they say that we will take a shower . I do that . I leave my clothing and I leave what whatever little possession I have of my own that I carry through all the year of camp , and these possession be a little handkerchief in which I have tie photograph of my brother and my parent , and after that we be really give shower and when the shower be over , make out ... make to go out through another door where we be give new strip uniform and uh and uh wooden shoe and all those thing that we leave behind we have never see again , so I have not have a picture of my parent until I come to the United States where my aunt uh give I a picture of my parent when they be first marry . this uh ... I remember they only vaguely that way , and I have no picture of my brother . we work .", "we be in Flossenburg for about six week . work very hard and one time we be expose to a selection . uh selection be a process where everybody stand naked and the a few ss people , one of they I believe a physician , kind of go by and mark we with a green ink write number or some symbol on we forehead and he do it to I too . I do not know what it mean and we do not know or we do not care anyway . do not know , do not care , but that night again we group be assemble , put on a train ... that group of four hundred and fifty .", "we have wooden shoe and we march make a tremendous clatter on the street . it be early in the morning and as we be be march people be , who be go to work , civilian , be stop . the trolley car be stop and people be stop to let we pass , a column of a few hundred people in strip uniform . -lrb- cry -rrb- and the people cry . -lrb- cry -rrb- for the first time I see support .", "he might have be a sr man , but I seem to remember he be a soldier . -lrb- Clearing throat -rrb- sorry . and he have a rifle there with a bayonet , a naked bayonet plant in ... uh ... the ... uh ... what you call that ? ... the ... uh ... on top of the rifle plant there . and as we come in , he jump mother and he see a woman with ... with a child there and he immediately decide we be jewish and he shoot at something like .", "we have to go through the shower . they shave we head in case somebody will run away they should find -lsb- she -rsb- , they should know that we be the Jews from the concentration camp , recognize we . they give we strip clothes with number . from then on we never be call by the name , only by the number . then they put we in barracks .", "they , it would be much easier for they and they provide special blue bus . at that time we do not know what be happen to they , but they be chase through certain 01:15:30 section of town into the forest , a place call Rumbola and there russian prisoner of war have prepare large grave , mass grave , and when the people get there they be tell to undress , put they shoe in one pile they shoe in one pile , clothing in another pile , drive to the edge of this mass grave , and machine-gunned . it be go on all night and the next day . fifteen thousand of we people be massacre in that particular day .", "perhaps , perhaps the Russians will be liberating we before the german have a chance to kill we . in the meantime , periodically the Germans would come into we camp , line everybody up in front of a table where one of the Germans would sit . everybody have to undress naked and walk in front of he , and if there be something he would like on you body , any scar or anything like that , you go to the left , and leave mean certain death . and my father who be a invalid and who be with we at that time yet still on many occasion he would have be doom if he would not have somehow we be able to save he by not let he go into the line , by sneak he out . when once I remember my father be take out and and send to the left , and he be still stand there and wait the truck to take he away , and the german guard be walk back and forth , and as he turn he back I snuck in .", "answer -lrb- Adam -rrb- : now , you see , again on one of my trip when I be go over , you know , on the other side of Warsaw ghetto ... I be catch without my ... without the armband near the wall , near the wall by a Gestapo , by ss man . they arrest I , of course , and take I to the headquarters of the Gestapo in Warsaw which be outside of the Warsaw ghetto , in the polish sectioned area ... in the polish section . and uh they be very rude and uh , of course , after interrogation they take I to a room which be about eight by eight and the wall be full of fresh blood , red wall , and then they have uh wooden bench on the floor and into on top be break piece of glass cement into these bench and they , they use to force you to undress and beat you to death on those piece of broken glass . he say to I , you be go to undress and lay down on this . I say oh no .", "they arrest I , of course , and take I to the headquarters of the Gestapo in Warsaw which be outside of the Warsaw ghetto , in the polish sectioned area ... in the polish section . and uh they be very rude and uh , of course , after interrogation they take I to a room which be about eight by eight and the wall be full of fresh blood , red wall , and then they have uh wooden bench on the floor and into on top be break piece of glass cement into these bench and they , they use to force you to undress and beat you to death on those piece of broken glass . he say to I , you be go to undress and lay down on this . I say oh no . I know ... why should i. .", "I have no chance ... you know I do not have any chance . I have no ar ... no gun . I could not help myself , but I say no , I will not undress . if you want you try . I feel that if he would try to undress I , I would start , you know , hit he and then he will just kill I at once and that be it , but uh I do not and he say to I , ok .", "I could not help myself , but I say no , I will not undress . if you want you try . I feel that if he would try to undress I , I would start , you know , hit he and then he will just kill I at once and that be it , but uh I do not and he say to I , ok . we just want to scare you . tomorrow we finish you .", "so a lot of people have clothes . and they come to I . I do not have ... I come home naked like my mother have I when I be bear . I be 2 week without . I go out in a blanket .", "they take they to the crematorium , but they do not have room for they . every 4 week they make selection . Mengele come in , and we have to strip all we clothes . we be naked . we have to pick up one hand and ... uh ... to ... go through .", "every 4 week they make selection . Mengele come in , and we have to strip all we clothes . we be naked . we have to pick up one hand and ... uh ... to ... go through . .", "so he tell I , `` Toby , I go ask the man . you know , mother , grandmother to child come to take bath too . '' so I say , `` you be naked . how could you go talk to a man . '' I be embarrass to go .", "so none of that change . there be no change . uh what you carry with you , unless you be totally degrade ... uh what happen in concentration camp where you be absolutely strip of everything , of dignity , but as long as you can keep you dignity , the fact that you be poor and you do not have clothing and that you have to be careful and so forth , do not matter . absolutely do not matter . you can carry you human dignity whether you be in a slum or whether you be in a plush , plush castle , or vice versa .", "they take my father 's wooden leg off and search it for money , contraband . but we know better than that , because by that time we already have learn we lesson . uh ... they take and strip my mother , totally naked , and check in place you would not dream of checking , and they take my little sister who at that time be a 8 year old kid , and strip she . I do not know exactly how much they check she , but I know my mother tell I that she be totally and utterly check . and then they put we back together again , we luggage and so forth , and we get to Italy .", ". with , you know , like tut , tut , tut , tut , tut , like this . and we do have to undress ourselves . in one mountain be the ... the ... the clothes , the ... the coat , and one mountain be the shoe , and one mountain be jewelry . there be a box with jewelry .", "do you have bla , bla , bla . '' and if you do not give it to they , then they search and that be worse . and then I be stand then in the front and he tell I to undress . to undress naked . naked !", "and if you do not give it to they , then they search and that be worse . and then I be stand then in the front and he tell I to undress . to undress naked . naked ! and you know , I do not want to do it , but my mother speak in latvian to I , `` do it .", "and then I be stand then in the front and he tell I to undress . to undress naked . naked ! and you know , I do not want to do it , but my mother speak in latvian to I , `` do it . do it . ''", "and you know , I do not want to do it , but my mother speak in latvian to I , `` do it . do it . '' she stay in back of I and she say , `` undress , '' in latvian to I . and I undress . I be just in my panties .", "do it . '' she stay in back of I and she say , `` undress , '' in latvian to I . and I undress . I be just in my panties . and he tell I to take a chair and to get up on the stove .", "-- `` all Jews out fast , fast ! '' with a beating . and we have see , among the ss , people in striped uniform , prisoner strip uniform . and these be the boy that work the railroad track . of course we do not know why .", "they shove we into the huge brick building , and there be prisoner and ss tell we what to do next . there be table , long table . the first area we have to undress , strip we clothing . there be hook behind we . you put the clothing through a piece of wire , hang the clothing up .", "they give we , issue we a striped brown cap , a jacket , a striped jacket , a pair of striped trousers , a pair of wooden clog , and a shirt . no sock or underwear . then the last area , when they give we the uniform , they give we two strip of cloth . the cloth I would say be about six inch long , maybe inch and a half wide . and it would star , star with the star of David , correspond with the number on you left forearm , sew on you left breast and on the right pant leg .", "the last one be Fisher , who die uh last year . and without a partner you could not survive . after we finish a day 's work at Canada Kommando , you just could not go home , back to the camp , without be search , first at the work site - line up , strip naked in most case . and if you be not strip naked , you pants drop because they know that some of we carry money in the place that be , uh , kind of dark . uh , but we do , we also know how to smuggle out , smuggle the stuff in .", "and without a partner you could not survive . after we finish a day 's work at Canada Kommando , you just could not go home , back to the camp , without be search , first at the work site - line up , strip naked in most case . and if you be not strip naked , you pants drop because they know that some of we carry money in the place that be , uh , kind of dark . uh , but we do , we also know how to smuggle out , smuggle the stuff in . for instance , you in this row , and you friend be in the row in front of you .", "ok . here on this end , I be one of the person unload the belongings of hungarian jew that be bring there , May 1944 , that already be gas . this come from the zunda -lrb- ph -rrb- , from the gas chamber , from the undress room . this photo , by the way , be give to I by historian , czech historian , czechoslovakian historian , jewish man . he name be Erich Kulka .", "of course , we do not know when the selection would be . but all of a sudden , in most case on a Sundays , cause everyone be in , in the camp . the whole camp be take out to Appellplatz , to roll call place , line up in row of five , strip naked , and you clothing be drop by you in front of you foot . and Mengele , with the , with the Lager ... Lager\u00e4ltester , who be a prisoner , and the Lagerf\u00fchrer , and also the commandant ; they would go from barrack to barrack , block to block . and behind Mengele be a prisoner registrar -- a Schreiber what they call -- and as Mengele would , this be how , how it would be .", "so then he take away the gun from my nose and he take off the the belly and tell I stand up . and I stand up so that ... take off you clothes . entirely naked I stand and then they could see that I be a jew and then he tell I if you escape from Kovno from the Nazis , what be you do here ? we already liberate Kovno five day . so I say ... I could see that they be very top up top officer of the army , but he look to I like a jew but he do not disclose a word about he jewishness , so he say , why do not you go back to Kovno .", "Q : be that right ? a : I never see a battle at night and I better explain that why . because to drive the tank you get to have some kind of uh , some light or something ... I mean you can not just go down without something on and if you show ... there be a little strip of light , and if you would show a strip of light , you would be shoot at . so that always bewilder I about people say they fight . now I be out on patrol at night .", "not the same dress , but the same material , and they hair be beautiful , long . young woman , very , very attractive woman . and they have a book , and they put we name in and then they give we tatoo and then we be with they go into a circle of soldier with big dog and then we have to take off we clothes , strip . the one who strip I , help I strip , take at the same time my wedding band off my finger . I have forget I have it .", "young woman , very , very attractive woman . and they have a book , and they put we name in and then they give we tatoo and then we be with they go into a circle of soldier with big dog and then we have to take off we clothes , strip . the one who strip I , help I strip , take at the same time my wedding band off my finger . I have forget I have it . maybe I would have try to put it in my mouth or whatever .", "I do not remember the other one , but one girl she be german . when I get out from there , he be stand right there . we be naked . can you imagine how a person feel , especially a woman , in front ... no matter how ... how bad the situation be , whatever ... I mean we practically lose we mind at ... at moment like that . but still the fact that we be naked in front of a man whoever it may have be , it be devastate and especially for a teenager that be modest .", "we be naked . can you imagine how a person feel , especially a woman , in front ... no matter how ... how bad the situation be , whatever ... I mean we practically lose we mind at ... at moment like that . but still the fact that we be naked in front of a man whoever it may have be , it be devastate and especially for a teenager that be modest . and when I see that i. . .", "uh , but , uh , railroad work be probably among the hardest work that we ever do because people be not strong enough to lift up the rail , and uh , some people get crush under the rail , and people fall down . we clothing be uh , uh , limit . in the wintertime we have clog on , we have shoe with wooden sole , blue/white strip uniform . in the beginning we have we own with the star of David on it . later on we get the blue/white-striped uniform .", "some of we might be shoot in the process of escape , if it be find out , but some of we might get through . so it always better in a group , then split up once you be outside . O.K. Uh , we have at that time plan if we get away from the factory , but then be , once you get , we have blue/white strip uniform , and what , what do you do when you escape . you be in the middle of Germany or some place or polish border or something . my idea be to get to my german friend , this catholic family by the name of sonnon -lrb- ph -rrb- in muchenglablak -lrb- ph -rrb- , whose parent be friend of my parent , to get to the house and then to survive the war in they cellar .", "but then the question be , once you escape , a tattooed number on the arm and uh hair shear . in other word , you look like a prisoner . and blue/white strip uniform that you could throw away if you have other clothes , but you still look like a prisoner with no hair and look like a skeleton , you be immediately recognize , so where you go to go . so even if you have a chance to escape , and the chance be there frankly , at the place of work , in , in the synthetic gasoline factory . there be many chance .", "at that time it would have be very easy to escape during the bombing . where to go ? hair shear off , number on the arm , and blue/white strip uniform . no place to go . no .", "First of all , it be freezing in there . uh , I be talk about the beginning of 1945 , the mid-winter , when we start there . and I ask this german engineer if he have any old clothing he could bring in that we could wear under we prisoner blue/white strip uniform and he say yes he would . and I say I have a friend too , and I say he would bring in some warm clothing . so he be one of the good guy .", "they be all about we age and they be all make it sort of , like we do , be able to stand up on they own two leg . and we say , we shall escape together . and they also have get civilian clothes like we do from some other place they be work , they be wear underneath they blue/white strip uniform . and , uh , so we say , well we will try and escape and then we go in different direction , maybe two one way , two another way , maybe one ss guard be firing , maybe he will hit some of we , maybe he will not hit anybody . but some of we will get out .", "there be nobody to touch sexually to begin with , but those year , they be animal . they do not care who they touch , they really do not . they touch I to see it my body 's naked , you know , just whatever I have on I to cover I up . they take off whatever they have on they back and they cover I , which be the truth . and I be -- they be watch I , also , same story .", "even the circumstance that we live in , we have no period . so that eliminate about how can we protect ourselves , if we do not have a period ? and they dig a long narrow strip outside , with a board across . that be we toilet , outside . and there be day when it be like 30 below zero .", "we have not have shower or bath or anything , or toilet paper , or anything . so , they chase we into a room . we be totally naked . they put up a table . it be like a fashion show table , like a runway .", "they put up a table . it be like a fashion show table , like a runway . and we have to walk naked on that table . and the ss man -- they sit on both side , and they look at we body , whether we be worthwhile saving , or be gas . I have this horrible rash , that I know I be go to be gas , because the gas be for -- the rash be from malnutrition and dirt .", "a : in Poland they do a resistance . but they do not succeed . you can not resist , when you be naked . do you know what I mean ? it be like take a person , and undress the person and say , `` fight for you life . ''", "you can not resist , when you be naked . do you know what I mean ? it be like take a person , and undress the person and say , `` fight for you life . '' with what ? there be nothing , never .", "and I enter the door , and I look . inside the room -- as I say a small room -- the Germans have erect some kind of a board upright , much like a sheet of plywood . and here , they have take a prisoner and they have strip he ; and they have nail he with spike -- common spike with the head on they -- through he elbow and through he wrist that I see . nail he like this , spread-eagled on that board . and I could see where they have take apparently a scalpel , and they have cut he throat on the side here ... he vocal cord somewhere .", "we leave half of the people dead . and other be mad . there be a woman whose child be kill and she be run naked and she do not know what be go on . and we have to run . I lose my sister , I lose my father .", "my father be separate from we when they separate man from woman . and I find myself in a room with many young woman . we be tell to undress . and I find my sister there . and this be Majdanek .", "and I find my sister there . and this be Majdanek . so we be tell to undress and leave everything behind we except we shoe , we could take we own shoe , which we do . we go through the shower . we be give some clothes .", "we be still fresh , we be okay . across from we at that time be the man 's lager . and we could see one day there be a selection of the man , which mean that the man stand in row naked and be file before the german to be move , to be destroy . at that point , I be 14 . for the first time in my life that I see a naked man .", "and we could see one day there be a selection of the man , which mean that the man stand in row naked and be file before the german to be move , to be destroy . at that point , I be 14 . for the first time in my life that I see a naked man . it be indecent , but the implication of what the selection be all about do not hit I at that time , you know , younger man , older man , different type of work . we be tell that the man lager be go to be move and that we , from the Birkenau Lager A , be go to move to Birkenau Lager B , where the man use to be .", "we be line no . we be on one side , tetrush -lrb- ph -rrb- prisoner of the administration create a cordon on the other side . we have order to undress completely and go over in front of the selecting officer . and tell to go left or right ; leave to life , right to death . and the one selection day , I be rotten from the waist down , infection , boil .", "and the one selection day , I be rotten from the waist down , infection , boil . the combination of poor diet , poor hygiene , what have you , just develop in boil . I be not go to undress . if I do , it be a death warrant . I decide I be go to undress on top but not at the bottom .", "I be not go to undress . if I do , it be a death warrant . I decide I be go to undress on top but not at the bottom . I try to go once and be push back , undress . 01:51:04 I do not .", "if I do , it be a death warrant . I decide I be go to undress on top but not at the bottom . I try to go once and be push back , undress . 01:51:04 I do not . I go again , I be certain I be go to death , I be pass to right .", "Enough this the clothes . you take the clothes off . and when I go to the right side , naked , they throw the Gestapo throw clothes to people who be to get off the left side and throw one shoe small , one piece clothes , nothing you can wear . Q . so after you get in this line , where do they take you ?", "so , you know , we live with hope that maybe we be go to live . they bring we into Maidanek . after a long , long drive they bring we into Maidanek , and they tell we to undress and to take a shower . they put we into cold shower and they take away everything . they give we old junk to put on we , and they take away all we jewelry but you see before we leave we be smarter , we put all the jewelry in the toilet .", "we be sit on it so we put everything there . we say let 's not give anything to they . but I forget that I have long hair and I forget that I have my earring with my monogram in my ear and my hair cover it , so it go through , but everything go and we be naked . the man , they take separate and they undress the man naked and they leave they only the strap in the hand and they tell they to hold the strap in they hand and they let german shepherd after they . and you know , when you have something in the hand and the german Shepherds go wild and they be bite out piece of meat of the people .", "we say let 's not give anything to they . but I forget that I have long hair and I forget that I have my earring with my monogram in my ear and my hair cover it , so it go through , but everything go and we be naked . the man , they take separate and they undress the man naked and they leave they only the strap in the hand and they tell they to hold the strap in they hand and they let german shepherd after they . and you know , when you have something in the hand and the german Shepherds go wild and they be bite out piece of meat of the people . this be the beginning of Maidanek .", "a : we be watch . the woman be separate , but the man be run . we be naked , we do not have strap . men have pants with strap so they have the strap and the german shepherd tear they apart . so , we go into the camp .", "a : less , less , it be worse . First of all they make selection every few week . they look at you naked . you have to go through naked with you clothes on you arm and they look you through like cattle and look at you tooth , exactly like cow like cattle , they be buy cow to work . so , they look we through from the front and from the back and they go around we like you know look all over you .", "First of all they make selection every few week . they look at you naked . you have to go through naked with you clothes on you arm and they look you through like cattle and look at you tooth , exactly like cow like cattle , they be buy cow to work . so , they look we through from the front and from the back and they go around we like you know look all over you . this be selection , call selection , and they select if you be still good to work they send you straight ahead and if not they take you out on the side .", "it be not civilization . it be , I think in the old age , they have a better civilization that we have . german look we over naked like piece of meat . we do not have we period time because they put something in you food that we be not woman . Q : how do you know that ?", "a : I have no idea . it be a few block . they fill up a few block and they keep we naked for about three or four week . I do not even know how long they keep we there because people use to come to we window from there and they use to see in one girl come , who she be my brother 's friend and she look at I and she think I be my other sister , , and she say be you , and I say who be you and she say it be Sophie Biaz . she be polish .", "she bring I a piece of bread into the window and she say do you know what happen to I ? she be very tall and very she have very gorgeous leg , she say you know what I do not have my cartlidge by my bone and I can only walk five or ten minute most and my foot , I do not have any feeling in my leg so she be a guinea pig there . she help I there a little and they keep we there and they feed we there naked and we be on the bed do nothing and just you know kid around and not know even what be go to bring tomorrow . we do not know . be we go to stay here , nobody know .", "we be lock in and no clothes so that be okay . we have a blanket you know like one blanket of eight and that be okay . we have a little something to cover ourselves and we be walk around naked . so , it do not bother we because we be all woman and we do not have anything to hide . we do not have anything period .", "for about three month we have to be there because people use to get sick and a lot of they die , a lot . so , we use to be in a quarantine and every Sunday people from the city learn about it and they come to we be in with big fence but people go through the fence and they talk and they ask we question and they speak very well english and german , so one couple come to the and they see I and they say we be surround around three way with water . it be a lake , and you could swim but naked . the boy find out that these girl be swim naked so they come to see we naked there and so a couple come , a young couple , she be in the forty maybe forty and she look and she say would you like to be free and go out from the quarantine , and I say of course I would . so , she say I can make you a passport and you can get out .", "so , we use to be in a quarantine and every Sunday people from the city learn about it and they come to we be in with big fence but people go through the fence and they talk and they ask we question and they speak very well english and german , so one couple come to the and they see I and they say we be surround around three way with water . it be a lake , and you could swim but naked . the boy find out that these girl be swim naked so they come to see we naked there and so a couple come , a young couple , she be in the forty maybe forty and she look and she say would you like to be free and go out from the quarantine , and I say of course I would . so , she say I can make you a passport and you can get out . I be go to be you foster mother and we can adopt you so she do .", "and when I come there I do not really know what happen . after a while a guard come and take I out and into the yard and to the shower . I have to undress and my clothes be disinfect and I have to shower . and then after the clothes come back , my suit and so on , be all trample they take I -- the guard take I to the first -- no , second floor of the prison and take I to a cell . I do not remember the number of the cell .", "he wear a yellow armband with black lettering on which be it say , - -- elderstedt , and then there be some other , you know , prisoner in striped uniform with armband . some have block elderstedt which mean block senior , and we be march to the shower . there we have to undress and we be shave all over we body include we head , and then we have to go into a tank which be full of some chemical , disinfectant , we have to submerge in it , and then from there we go to the shower and we have to wash , and when we come out of the shower , we have to put we civilian clothes , because when we come from the prison we be still in civilian clothes . we have to -- it be pack in a bag , in a paper bag with we number . of course , we do not have the number then but after the shower then we be issue prison uniform .", "we have to -- it be pack in a bag , in a paper bag with we number . of course , we do not have the number then but after the shower then we be issue prison uniform . we get long underwear , striped , you know , blue and white stripe but very , very narrow underwear , and then we receive striped , one-inch white striped , white and blue trousers and jacket and a cap , also strip . then we be issue to swatch of white cloth with a number . my number be 13390 and two red triangle .", "you could only see the foreyard , you know , to the crematorium . there be a gate and then there be a small yard and to this from we window where we be at the far end of this block . I see myself a truck arrive and back out to the gate to the small yard and Jews have to - only man - they arrive from the truck and be put into the yard and there they have to undress . now , how do I know they be Jews ? because , because they be hasidic Jews .", "they wear special dress . you know , mostly black , black hat and most of they have beard . later on , we also find out from the crematorium people who have to burn the body that there be Jews from the polish city of Bendzin , which be in Syvicia -lsb- ph -rsb- not far from Auschwitz , and these people have to undress and they disappear . I could not see that , but they all go to the gas chamber there and they be gas . now , as I work in the carpentry a time and then in the workshop you know I have to take order and the order come to I , and I have to distribute the order to the different workshop , you know whether it be a order for the locksmith or a order for the carpenter or for the glasser or for the electrician and so on .", "we know something be go on . later on , they bring maybe 100 , I do not know exactly , 100 man . now , they be strip to the waist but you could see from the trousers that they be soldier . as I say , later on we do find out that they be russian soldier . it as also after the invasion , after the June 22 , 1941 , I think it be in August , and they , they be register or question or whatever the ss - nobody .", "it be a very small one - room apartment . there be no privacy . I remember my mother basically sponge bathing in a little basin of water she would stand in and I remember see she naked in the room . I mean , there be no other place to go . so , to literally you live there , you sleep there , you cook there and so forth , but my father suddenly become a farmer .", "and the truck never arrive at the ghetto . we be tell by the ss that the truck have be take to Dunamenda -lrb- ph. -rrb- for the people to work at the canning factory . and , in fact , there be no such thing as Dunamenda and the truck be take directly into the wood which we find out only later and the people have to strip and be shoot into open mass grave . all this , of course , we find out later . meanwhile , we settle down in the house or shack that be assign to we because the ghetto be in the worse slum area of Lega .", "we be save , we be singing . and we have to go to selection , you know . so one side we carry we stuff and we be naked . in one hand , we have to be like up , and we be check if we be clean , or we do not have some wound . you know , thing like that .", "I mean this be normal to think that if you do not see anybody and you know that six people be away and you know that you be select , so you think that you will die . and those six people after they finish the grave , they see the six people who run away be bring in . those people be disrobe , be naked . the original six people be catch on the road and bring back . this nobody know at that time .", "the original six people be catch on the road and bring back . this nobody know at that time . and they make they run through the barb wire where they escape naked . there be four woman and two man . and instinctively they cover they private part and they do not let they .", "you have to be courageous , but it be very hard in a sense . so that when I think back really , if I would have to go through this again , I probably would not make it . so we be just practically naked , and my mom make for I a pair of sock from a empty bag of potato which use to be throw away from the kitchen . potato , pea . so I have a pair of pants make of a bag , and I do not have any shoe , so I have rag wrap around my foot .", "so they tell we you be go to be disinfect and shave . so everybody be shave up and down . men and woman naked go to the shower room , and the clothing be take to a disinfection place there . so we go naked into that shower room . we do not know what happen to the shower room , the gas chamber and all these thing .", "so everybody be shave up and down . men and woman naked go to the shower room , and the clothing be take to a disinfection place there . so we go naked into that shower room . we do not know what happen to the shower room , the gas chamber and all these thing . we do not know .", "those Jews , it be a tragedy . we still have something to wear , but they do not . they be , I would say , three-quarter naked . rag . and the soldier be beat they , .", "we be the only transport from L\u00f3dz Ghetto that do not go to Auschwitz ; he keep he word about that . Ravensbr\u00fcck , though , be a hell . we be strip of we clothes . we go through a medical examination , which be -- I can not even say the word `` embarrassing '' because the people who conduct it be less than human . they be less than animal .", "in that way we be very innocent . we be completely unaware of anything when we first come there . we experience with the selection , we have to stand naked in front of the -- I do not know -- doctor or whatever . you could not have a pimple on you body . you have to be perfect for work , and then look for the jewel , the vaginal experiment that -- it be -- the hell start right there .", "you could not have a pimple on you body . you have to be perfect for work , and then look for the jewel , the vaginal experiment that -- it be -- the hell start right there . we be strip of every , every human trace of behavior . the brutality , the killing , the sicc the dog -- the dog be sicc at the people . they be rip the people apart with the exception of I , I think .", "he play a concerto about Paris -lrb- `` An American in Paris '' -rrb- . and he play from `` Porgy and Bess '' , and just tear the house down . and I see Stupel present Bernstein with a Dachau strip haftle shirt , prisoner shirt , with the jewish star on it . and he weep . he be so profoundly affect .", "02:07:17 so they tell they , the first thing , take off the jacket . after -- and the overcoat , then the jacket . and 'til they come to the end , they be naked . and they be in line to go , they be put in the concentration camp , in the chamber , the gas chamber . I see the gas chamber before they start to build because I be there and be do some work there .", "thanks to the gold coin , food , you could obtain food during Ghetto time and get better accommodation for some good means to sustain yourself with gold coin . at that time , this be a very tragic time , because then Germans come they bring dog in the Ghetto , and they be go from house to house to look to see if you turn in all gold , and if you do not hide . and they even take some people to undress they completely , some woman to undress and the dog be train go and lick they sexual organ to make sure there be no coin of gold hide . Q : excuse I , what be that ? a : they have dog train , they use to take certain woman , tell they to undress completely , and the dog with its tongue would lick they sexual organ of the woman to find if they put any gold coin there .", "and they even take some people to undress they completely , some woman to undress and the dog be train go and lick they sexual organ to make sure there be no coin of gold hide . Q : excuse I , what be that ? a : they have dog train , they use to take certain woman , tell they to undress completely , and the dog with its tongue would lick they sexual organ of the woman to find if they put any gold coin there . Q : do you know people that this happen to ? a : yes I do .", "and they say to we , `` okay , go into this large area and disrobe . '' I mean by disrobe take everything off . so , here I be next to my mother , hundred of woman , and we have to be totally naked come in in front of a desk with a bunch of young hoodlum . so , what do you think in a case like that . they be creature from another planet .", "there be no planet then , but creature from hell . why should I bother worry about they , whether they look at I . how demeaning can you even feel stand with you mother and relative and family -- my sister-in-law -- and here you be stand totally naked , and they look at you . so , I just stand there , and they just look at we , and they tell we to go in the back to take shower , and they give we the uniform , the striped uniform , and this be how we ordeal start . this be concentration camp .", "Q : be you hit ? a : I be never hit , because I work . I tell you I just decide at one time , especially when I be stand there naked , that these be devil from some place , and I be go to look at they as such . so , this be my -- I brainwash myself . I figure they be not go to bring I down to they level .", "you can take my ring , you can take my watch , whatever I have , but please leave we here on the street , do not take we . '' so that be what happen . they strip we of everything we have and leave we in the corner of that street by the door of some building . so here we be , about twelve o'clock in the afternoon with nowhere to go , with nowhere to sleep , with no money . soon enough we have no choice but to try to find a way to get into the ghetto .", "they be teach how to make woman 's hair net . it be a fashionable thing at that time to do . they be take the car inner-tube or truck inner-tube and cut into small strip , very narrow strip . then they could buy white silk and then they be die the silk different color . be it a gold , gray , brown or black or navy blue .", "as a matter of fact , they hear about the other farm and they take care of he already . they go that night before they come to we . they wake up the whole family , the farmer refuse we entry ask he to strip completely from the waist down . Bent over a trunk of a tree and so on they beat he up with some ... branch of tree and so on . 06:09:02 they be bleed .", "he bring in he and in walk a pair of german britch . you know what the britch ; be ride pants . bind together on top , so I pull the cord , fall down , naked stand the little boy . this little boy must have be six , seven . he must be ten , something like that .", "and Wassileskov -lrb- ph -rrb- be the commandant . a fairly young man , I would say probably no more than 45 , and he march around with a whip and when he find a louse on a person , that person get 25 in front of everybody else , over they behind . over they naked behind . so when I hear of Singapore I be no longer very impressed you know . so , what else can I tell you ?", "we be first of all we be two year in a ghetto in Ozerkoff . so , they want less people , so one day we be assemble in the school auditorium , man , woman , and child . there be Nazis in front of we and we be tell to strip naked and parade in front of they . they look we over like a bunch of cattle and we be stamp like a bunch of cattle with a letter a or b . we be tell to get dress , go home , and wait for further order .", "the younger people they leave use they for work . those be the people that go away . Q : now , just tell I when you be stand naked in front of all of these Nazis have to parade around , that must have be a very unusual experience . I be wonder if it be more difficult for the girl ? a : I think I be shock because I have never see a naked male , not even my own brother .", "Q : now , just tell I when you be stand naked in front of all of these Nazis have to parade around , that must have be a very unusual experience . I be wonder if it be more difficult for the girl ? a : I think I be shock because I have never see a naked male , not even my own brother . it be shocking . I just look around myself and see everybody walk ahead so I figure this be what I have to do , try to shield yourself , you know part of you body because it be so embarrassing .", "it be call in polish halumintzfau -lrb- ph -rrb- . she could bring the work home . she be tear all kind of rag apart , make strip , braid the strip and fashion rug . what they need that for , I have no idea , but that be what she be do and every day she have to make a certain amount and deliver it the same day . so that be the work we be do there .", "so , he stand hesitated and push I towards she . over there again , we have to line up move forward closer towards the shower . before we enter we have -- walk farther down the line we be tell to strip naked and this on line always in five they look we over again , anyone that have a birth mark or a scar from surgery or some woman if they be middle age that survive the first selection and have some wrinkle on they body , be also take out of this line . from then , before they take we into the shower , they shave the hair on we body . every place a person have hair have be shave .", "and he come out , we see he , we give he we signal , we start to cough . he look around , he look up , he see we . he get back into the camp and tell the captain he get two refugee from a concentration camp and they be naked . and the captain say come in . he call we in , we come down , we go into the office and the captain look at we and give he a paper and he take we to the PX .", "they bring in representative from the neutral country , Sweden , Switzerland . they bring in the people -- representative , and they start to dig those gr -- mass grave -- those grave . and because the Russians , when they shoot those prisoner of war , they do not do it like the Germans do where they make they undress , shoe go to shoe , pants go to pants , jacket go to jacket , hair be shave . they remove jewelry . I mean , the Germans be quite methodical in they killing .", "Q. tell I about it , for people who do not see the movie . a . there be this -- you know when you come to Auschwitz the first time , that there be the -- they rob you completely naked , and you go in these shower room , but you do not know if it come out water or come out gas . the people , you do not know . and you be stand there , three hundred woman , and you be look upstairs , and we do not know what they be go to _______ .", "t : delousing . b : delousing . so the train would arrive and the patient would be take out from the train , take off , strip from the clothes , shave they hair and they clothes be disinfect , and the train be disinfect . there be two team work . there be the jewish team work on the dirty side and there be a lithuanian team work on the clean side .", "a. Yanosko , Limberg . they shave we and then you hear this scream because they ask everybody to open they mouth and they have like gold crown , they just knock it out , which be terribly painful . they just undress we . men , woman , child . it be almost unhuman .", "it be almost unhuman . then they push we to different barracks and when evening or at night when they build a fire and there like a ____________ which be like a heap and then they put a big fire and while we be sit there , you could see the fire . it be not a recreational fire , it be quite a large area and the flame be go up and with they rifle they be point to people give they instruction to dress , to undress , whatever there be , one gown you be wear and to throw himself on the burning . there be a mother and a daughter sit near I . I do not think the daughter maybe be 14 or 15 year of age .", "there be a mother and a daughter sit near I . I do not think the daughter maybe be 14 or 15 year of age . he point out only to the mother and when the mother be still undress , the daughter quickly get up and undressed and follow she , and many other perish the same way . sometimes they would take we out and they would have those vicious dog and when they find out that somebody be a rabbi , I remember one be a priest even who try to hide the jewish child , and push the dog and you could see how the flesh be come off these people . sometimes they hang the people and the jewish boy who be in control .", "we use to get enough ammunition of theirs , but that be hard . now , after the first battle line be over , we command order we to go back to position , only change position because we expect that this will not be the last battle . so all of these kill , include the Zundenfeur -lrb- ph -rrb- , the officer , we command order to go ahead , to strip they uniform off of they and just naked and cover with a blanket , put they back on a horse and wagon and we take one of the farmer , send they to the city to turn in they corpse and give they a note , `` do not fight we , because that be the way you be go to see the rest of you come back . '' it be true enough that we be there and the follow day the commander decide that we should be on guard again because they probably will send in a second force . and they do .", "I : I just remember something that for year , even today sometimes that besides you -- you know , you just say the smell . yes , it always be -- there be a awful smell there . it be horrible all the time , but what I remember be wait in line naked . stand outside naked wait on line to get into the shower and sometimes we would stand out there for many hour it seem and somehow I remember that be scary , because I do not know now , but I know that sometimes you do not get you clothes at the end of this shower and you be not go to be able to come back . but again , be probably silly child , at one time I have a locket from my mother that I wear around my neck and I know that when we undress for the shower if anybody see this , it would be real trouble , but I be brazen enough to think that I could actually get away with hide this in my hand , so I do remember take it off my neck and hold it very tightly in my hand to get into the shower and I probably lose it then right in the shower because -- do not come out with it but I remember it be a act of defiance on my part .", "yes , it always be -- there be a awful smell there . it be horrible all the time , but what I remember be wait in line naked . stand outside naked wait on line to get into the shower and sometimes we would stand out there for many hour it seem and somehow I remember that be scary , because I do not know now , but I know that sometimes you do not get you clothes at the end of this shower and you be not go to be able to come back . but again , be probably silly child , at one time I have a locket fr