ake the better part of a day to get process there and again somebody come , a german prisoner and pick out the younger one and you go , you stay over here and among those be my brother and I try to yank he back to the group where I be and the guy spot it and he pull he out again . and then I try to go , I try to sneak into that group and he spot I and pull I back and I try one more time and he say , you try it one more time and you will get it . so that be the last time I see my brother .", "and he be a attorney in Munkacz and be a very nice person . and again that be fortunate for I that I meet he and that he be that nice . and after sort and be check by a ss doctor , again undressed naked and a floodlight on you to see what shape you be in and he pick out I do not know how many of we and we get assign to one barracks . we find out when we be there that we be work in tunnel on a rotate shift and eight hour shift and we shift happen to start on Sunday night at 11 . so it would be from 11 until 7 in the morning work in the tunnel .", "that be what I think about -- what we do so that they would have shoe . dp . and what they do , and what they do when they take the shoe off -- the Jews before go in the undress room -- before go into the crematoria . so worry that we man would not have shoe and they be so worried that they could not take ` em off fast enough . they be in the bin , be not they -- in the museum .", "I use to get a piece of bread , usually int he morning , with some black stuff to drink and I remember that I would always , since I be always -- maybe it be in the afternoon -- because I be always hungriest in the morning so I think it would be really clever for I to try to save this piece of bread so I would have it the next day and of course it usually be go and I do not understand it but now in retrospect I think the rat and mouse at Auschwitz must have love I . they know who to come to . I remember stand in line , humiliate standing outside in the cold naked wait to get into the shower and also terribly scared because somehow I know that you do not always come out of the shower . I do not know quite what happen , but I know you do not always come back . I be amaze at my , I guess call it chutzpa , because I have a locket on my neck , a gold locket from my mom and I be determine to hang on to this and of course if they have see it , I do not know what would happen to I , but I take it off my neck and hold on to in my hand and somehow get pass the guard .", "once I go to Berea and talk to the Berea class , and that be the worst . they be just uninterested , sleepy people with a professor who , himself , put I asleep . I just could not blame the student , by that time , they be so turn off , that no matter what I do , I could have strip nude , and it would not have make much of a difference in that class . but the middle-school kid , the junior high , they be just great to talk to . one girl ... just yesterday , I be speak to a class , and one little girl stay behind , and I usually spend about a hour and a half with they .", "I say , `` what be you talk about ? '' the german commander , they be stand in front of the tank , they tie they down evidently , I do not know . and they , with no medal , they strip they of all the medal , but I do not see that . I still see the Nazis , I say , `` what you talk about ? here they be . ''", "they have nothing . so , what happen with those rabbi , they take they out from the attic . they tell they to take off they clothes , all naked . they put they against that particular wall and they shoot they with the machine gun , they finish they up . Q .", "I have to look around what to do after the concentration camp . I be poor . I have nothing , almost naked , nothing to wear . I have to look around what to do . so , you know , I come out from it .", "the camp commander would come in who be a drunkard and a sadist . he would come in every day , pick out ten man and beat they up . tie they to a pole , naked , and whip they with he horse whip , the whip he use for he horse . just to show the rest of we . we be about 4,000 in there .", "we start to die in that barn . epidemic of typhoid , dysentery , hunger . every morning the guard order the little bit healthier woman to take out the dead and dress they naked cause the clothes you can recycle and dump the body in the hole . my dear friend , what my eye see , in those three week that I be in the barn , it be very hard to tell , to share , to describe . many time I feel I do not want to talk about it anymore but we be sit , this tape be for history , to learn the truth .", "we have nothing . because we be take from home . we be take to Shtoodruff -lrb- ph -rrb- , we be strip naked , we be not successful to bring anything , anything of we own through . some people that go back to Poland , let 's say if I would have be from Lodz , originally , maybe when I come back if I would have go to my old house , maybe I would have find something . also do not forget , many people come back to Poland and go to the little village and be kill because of that possession .", "Q : it seem to I that ... a : yeah , I , I do not know if I ever tell that story -lsb- talkover -rsb- but when we come -lsb- talkover -rsb- how important they be . when we come to Shtoodruff -lrb- ph -rrb- and we go through that shower so-called , and we stand outside for a long time naked and then we be give a dress , a pair of underpants , a pair of shoe . they just throw it to we . they do not say what size or whatever .", "one day this german woman , a nazi , uniform , I will never forget she name , she name be Berta , she be wear these leather boot and a whip , just flip around she whip against she boot and be point with the , with the whip to certain man and young boy , and only with , with , with good skin on they , that the rib be not expose , the bone be not expose , I have no idea why . and she point at I and my number be take down by 