 . but something I can not forget be that first day when we arrive , they have we undress completely because they be afraid we would bring sickness into Switzerland . I be 15 year old . I be there .", "I be 15 year old . I be there . my mother be naked . I be naked . and I see she misery .", "I be there . my mother be naked . I be naked . and I see she misery . that body .", "so they take I right away to the prison and then they take I to the Gestapo . and the whole day they interrogate I . they have I strip in the nude . they would not even let I go to the toilet . they follow I .", "but I will tell you , it -- it -- good thing come of it , because when they start -- when they start transport Jews to the death camp of Lvov , and you know , and -- and -- of Beljets , and -- and -- and other camp , some people break the little window in the boxcar open , and throw child out , or youngster get out . so quite often , people knock on the door , and specifically I remember th -- a fellow that later become one of the best partisan , one of the best sharpshooter that we have , Moishe lot , he die three year ago . he come , knock to the door , he be stark naked , stark naked . he say , `` let I in , I be very cold , and I want to go in with you tomorrow to work . '' so I take he in , I give he something to eat , he warm up , and I give he some clothing , and in the morning he blended in with the group , and go to camp .", "let I lighten it for you , and tell you again a story that you will get a chuckle of . we , as I tell you before , be stay in the forest in dig -- in dug-out , in -- in deep basement , you know , with a stove inside , it be warm . you know , you could undress and sleep comfortably . but as far as physical need , to go to the toilet and what have you , you have to go outside . so what we do be we take a plank of wood , and we tie it , or nail it , you know , if we have nail , most case we tie it between two tree , so a person can sit down , and , you know , do whatever he need to , and come back .", "she see the passport . they examine I . I have to undress . it be a woman . and I have -- I still have it , I have to show you .", "I be sure a lot of woman ... I do not want to explain how the other woman be look when I see they . Q : explain it . a : somebody be naked , and some of they be mentally . absolutely mentally . a : mentally ill ?", "Q : how be the inmate dress ? a : very , very poorly . many of they naked . Q : any type of uniform ? a : no .", "a : be take over . Bousch be in command , and he instruction be no food , no nothing until the medic get there . they have gather in the town of Linz quite a lot of garment for both male and female and have pass those out so that these people that be naked have something to put on . Q : and they be strong enough to dress themselves ? a : not all of they , no .", "but I carry that in my pocket wherever I go . even to Paris when the war be over . I would feel naked without it . Q : how do you feel when you return to the States ? a : a good example of that be that a friend of mine up in Ohio and I go to see the Cleveland Indians play a baseball game .", "rotting meat . you could see they be people . many of they be naked , and none of they have shoe . and then we walk inside and see these skinny people who be still live . we realize they be starve and we have nothing but some candy bar which we get in a ration , so one of my enlist man who walk in with I give a candy bar to one of these people .", "it be like a giant cesspool . the sturdiest structure in the camp be the weirdly efficient crematorium . outside of the crematorium , I see a long flatbed trailer load with four layer of naked , starve body . at least 200 tiny adult corpse , weigh 40 to 60 pound each , I guess , be stack and tie like cord wood await the oven . this gruesome shipment have be transport along the german highway almost cover with canvas , but open enough to see under .", "live prisoner be haul into the camp by rail and by truck . some be select for work in the factory while they life last ; the other be mark for final disposal take into a room with simulated shower head . they strip for the shower and be bolt into the room . the victim realize too late that gas , not water , come out of the nozzle . all the body be completely strip of jewelry , gold tooth , and any other item of value before be throw down a chute into the oven room .", "they strip for the shower and be bolt into the room . the victim realize too late that gas , not water , come out of the nozzle . all the body be completely strip of jewelry , gold tooth , and any other item of value before be throw down a chute into the oven room . there be a administration building in front of the entrance gate with lab for medical experimentation on human . many lamp of tattooed skin be show to I by the inmate in grisly display .", "2ibid . clothing burn off . they be naked . Q : do you see if they be man and woman , old , young ? a : as I recall it , they be man .", "just load with human body . most of they Jews , at this particular point in time . and all naked . they apparently have be cart from Warsaw or someplace in these boxcar , and the flatcar , of course , be stack with human body . the boxcar be open and when the door open , the one that be dead next to the door fall out on the ground .", "they apparently have be cart from Warsaw or someplace in these boxcar , and the flatcar , of course , be stack with human body . the boxcar be open and when the door open , the one that be dead next to the door fall out on the ground . as I walk past , and I could see inside the boxcar , just nothing but naked human body . as to the gas chamber , this be a very , very , clever system they have in which they would herd the one that be alive and this be they basic system of extermination . they would bring they into this place and there be the crematorium -- and I think it be even next door or adjoining -- and hand these prisoner a towel and a bar of soap and tell they to walk in that room which the sign say `` Showers '' .", "Q : this be the second picture which we will m ark `` B. '' tell we about it . a : in the block where the prisoner sleep on board ... the only thing I can liken it to be a broiler house like you might find here in Georgia , and there be either two or three tier of these shelve arrangement , just board lay down , and the prisoner sleep on those . each night as they die in they sleep or whenever they die in these block , there be detail that each morning take the dead to the end of the block and strip the clothes off of they and then they be move out into this storage area here . at least , this be where we find this pile of body . later , they be burn in the crematorium .", "and what be explain to I be that they bring russian prisoner in from the front in closed truck ; they have some sort of a way that they force they in there , in cordwood fashion , and they draw this top over they and that many of they by the time they get to Buchenwald be dead . they back the truck up to the crematorium where this chute that come down into the basement be , and as the body be push down the chute , any that be still move , they skull be crack with this club , and then they be hang at the base of the skull on these meat hook . they be strip of they clothes , they tooth be knock out and all the gold be render from they tooth , and then there be a cart on track that they load these body on . and a elevator arrangement , the detail of which be too vague to I now ... but this cart go up and these track down the center of this somehow ... Q : yes .", "of course , you know that when they describe torture and thing like this , you -- but -- but the -- the killing be not on the mass level that the thing that we encounter in -- in El Salvador . the -- the thing that -- that stru -- have strike I always in my work in human rights be the different -- that some of the people who commit these act have no -- no s-s -- I do not know , i-it 's not question of conscience , but if we -- j-just to give you a example , we -- we have one man who testify as a witness , have be involve in this , and we ask , be they tortured ? and he say , `` no , they be not tortured , '' but -- and we say , `` well you have this woman standing there for 24 hour naked in this cellar , try to get a confession in front of man . '' `` well , that be not torture . '' y-you know , the different notion of what be torture , if y -- if you do not hit somebody over the head , then it be okay .", "now this be a very , very rewarding thing for I . because if I start a thing , we be kill , and nobody do anything . and this time we be undress -- I be not talk I personally , but the Jews , and we be undr -- dress over a -- a -- a ditch , and we be kill . now if e-each one of they would think , if I would live and if I could pay they back , everybody will do it . now , after the war , people do not do it .", "take away my clothes . take away the clothing , take away I have picture from home , everything give away . go into shower one side , come out other side naked , give I other clothes and a different man , a different person . do they give you a striped uniform too or just ___ ? yeah , sure .", "take away my clothes . take away the clothing , take away I have picture from home , everything give away . go into shower one side , come out other side naked , give I other clothes and a different man , a different person . do they give you a striped uniform too or just ___ ? yeah , sure .", "they do not have too much to eat so they , from the guard , they come in , not all of they , whoever be duty-free and they be look by we . or sometimes , when we come in by the gate , count so they can pull you out . in the boot , this they be allow and to strip you and to look . sometimes you find money also . anything you be not allow you could find , otherwise , we be not able to survive and so on and so on .", "eight hundred people , well-dressed , _______ they bring they to we , 800 . when they bring they to we , so the ukrainian ______ I be a old calhoon but those arte the new one and they know , the Germans do not know so much as the Ukrainians , they know that they have money and so on and so on . go in from work , _____ , that be a new one , a ukrainian pull he out , strip he -- they strip once my uncle also . they come in , in the barracks . once , if the lagerfuhrer , that Fiess or he helper , adjutant , come in and see in the guard .", "as a matter of fact , just a week ago or two week ago . he work for the ss , he be very handy . he be give material to do for the -- either the wife of the ss or the german soldier I do not know -- like pin or book marker or little thing like that out of metal and leather strip . he make some for I and I save they . I have those various thing .", "Q : oh there be ? a : right , a football game be stage in one of the barracks . for that event , a trophy , be a leather strip and I see the picture in this book which be identical to what he make . it be find after liberation in camp , this item . I would say 99 % sure that he must have make that .", "the gate say like all camp , Arbeit Macht Frei which mean work make free . in the camp , I keep ask as we walk through the slau ______ -- . you be take to a place where you be search and strip which be call slau _______ , mean like a sluice . there be people work who be already in Terezin and I keep ask they if they know my brother . he be still there and then maybe a day or two later , I really do not remember , it take a day or two to locate he and see he .", "be these people derange ? what do you father see when he get out of that car ? a : he see the sign that `` Work make you free '' and he see there be a building that you go into to strip and get rid of all the clothing . they give you the prison clothing . Q : he do not see any dead people ?", "? a : until much later when they get a feel for the rhythm of the camp . Q : okay so together they get strip ? a : they get strip , they get shower . believe it or not they get shower , they get they haircut and they have to give up they shoe and they get they uniform .", "a : until much later when they get a feel for the rhythm of the camp . Q : okay so together they get strip ? a : they get strip , they get shower . believe it or not they get shower , they get they haircut and they have to give up they shoe and they get they uniform . they be tattoo I think .", "Lisa , you can come in , say whatever -- . -lcb- we also have to -- in all town . it be __________ , to put strip on the glass -rcb- oh , yeah strip on the glass . -lcb- on the glass from shatter , you know . in case it shatter in the bombing -rcb- .", "we come into Flossenburg iu July -- it be real hot , I think the middle of July . they take off all the clothes . we have to throw away the clothes , naked , you know , like you be bear . you be still in you regular civilian clothes , right ? no , no , no .", "she tell we what be go on over there in the cemetery when they bring the people . they have to dig they grave , a trench . they undress they and they shoot they with a machine gun . they fall down and the Poles be stay over there and take off the rest what be over there -- for sample , the stocking or the underwear . they rob they .", "they do not belong to you . they belong to David Bass what you kill he . I strip he naked and I tell he go home . everybody be clap . I know , you know , a shame .", "the way up to the camp 's entrance lead through a very steep road which to we , at that time be like scale Mt. Everest . we arrival at the shower coincide with a blackout due to a air raid alarm which last for most of the night . I remember a wave of naked body push towards the door and attendant , use high pressure hose with cold water , force we back to the wall , while those at the wall push we back again , and throughout all this there be dead body on the floor and they number increase . it be a night never to be forget . when release in the morning and assign to the quarantine barrack , it take almost another day before we receive the first morsel of food .", "Snow , it be the winter , it be no heat at all over there . I go over there one day , I want to see how this go on . like in the army , they undress and they go like a commission , from one doctor to another . you name this and that where you work . and I tell to he , listen , you can go free .", "do not worry about anything . everything be shrivel . he stay for half a hour over there , naked to wait for the doctor . do not think they will recognize who you be . this be what it be .", "they build , they put down bush in both end . in the center , it be like a cross-up , like a bridge . they bring the people over there naked . they let they out from the truck and they close the thing . the machine gun shoot they down .", "I do not know what the English be go to do with they , but help the english people fight Germany . and we want to sign up . when they take I for a medical examination , which they undress we completely . at that particular point in Cuzar I be reject because they find out that I be circumcise and I be jewish , not polish even though I speak polish and my uncle speak polish and we be bear in Poland , but because we be jewish they do not accept we . and they give I a document , in polish it be write _________ .", "I : well , we do have some stuff but ... I ... this be ... I ... the only thing I recall be that I have a locket . I have a locket that I ... a heart , and I remember have that for a long time even when I arrive in Auschwitz and I be very brazen . we would stand on line for the shower and we would have to strip naked and I have enough presence of mind to know that I have to take this thing off and I would hold on to it . I do not know how I do it , but I do it . I lose the locket however , somewhere .", "I do not have my twin -- because he be ... we be not of the same sex so it be a little harder . but throughout all the time in the hospital and through experiment and through horrible time , I always feel that Rene be alive and I say that I have to stay alive to take care of he . this be like my mission in life and I very clearly remember umm ... stand on line -- it be always cold , of course -- and we be go into the shower , stand naked and again . I bring up the locket -- for a long time , I be miraculously able to hang on , hide the fact that I have this locket , and always put it back on after I come out of the shower . I also remember that somehow I know already that not everybody come out of the shower , so every time we be line up like this , I remember that fear , like oh my God , be this the last time ?", "I be not there when the shower be build , but I understand that the day they put in the shower they evacuate . so I do not know about it . but it be build outside the camp so you would have to run out naked to take the shower and come back . Ok ? but I be not even there then .", "the death rate be very high . it be a awful camp . we work there on build a landing strip for german plane . I believe that be what it be . but in the meantime I learn one way to supplement the food and not to die of hunger .", ". we live in abandon farmhouse I remember . we also -- I be also put on -- they call Commando -- to a place call Rzekne and while I be there , I be ... I come in contact with Boleslav Michovsky who have become fairly well know in this country because he be the carpenter in Minneola that be accuse of the war crime -- as a war criminal and then I guess he lose -- be strip of he citizenship and be suppose to be deport and he be now on trial in Germany for he crime . probably now he be in he eighty so he will probably never ... never make it but in any event , that . .", "I do not speak Latvian -- I only speak german . I mean there be just no way . also we hair be crop close and through the middle we have a shaven strip that be re-shaven probably every two or three week so ... and the woman be completely shave . they head be completely shave so you would stand out from the population . I do not know how people ... I guess some people do get away -- you know , not many but I guess some people do .", "the Germans be try to carry back everything that they could carry back . I remember , we be dismantle even the tin roof -- put the sheet of tin in wooden enclosure and they be be ship back to Germany . they be just strip the place and we be there for ... that must have be late ' 44 , that must have be , I would say , early fall to late fall ' 44 , and we be there for several month do that particular thing . one of the unfortunate thing that happen there be that one of the russian bomb hit the building that we be in and probably fifteen or so of we be kill . uh .", "a : when I go to the right , they take I into the uh ... uh . . the camp , they take we to a barrack , to undress , leave everything , completly naked . then they take we to another place , where it be a cabin , a. . .", "Q : so this be in April 1944 ? a : 1944 . and , the ... when we go through that , we have to go outside completely naked in April , completely naked . we be stand there for a while , then all of a sudden , after we , woman - they get into the water and they come out naked - completly naked . and when i. .", "a : 1944 . and , the ... when we go through that , we have to go outside completely naked in April , completely naked . we be stand there for a while , then all of a sudden , after we , woman - they get into the water and they come out naked - completly naked . and when i. . .", "everything be recycle . Anthony : you never see any of these can with the original label on they ? they have already be strip of they label ? Hanna : whatever it be , it be strip . but they be around and they do help and when anything be available , they be use .", "Anthony : you never see any of these can with the original label on they ? they have already be strip of they label ? Hanna : whatever it be , it be strip . but they be around and they do help and when anything be available , they be use . Anthony : real kitchen be not available ?", "you have little bit , they would not take you . big guy , I be big but not big like they be . of course , I be skinny but -- we stay there naked and near the clothes , we still have private clothes . only mark it down with red , red mark , political prisoner , understand ? we put the suit on the side and we stay naked .", "of course , I be skinny but -- we stay there naked and near the clothes , we still have private clothes . only mark it down with red , red mark , political prisoner , understand ? we put the suit on the side and we stay naked . so they select somebody likes . so I see from 50 or 60 , they pull out one and go one side .", "I have a belt , a wide leather belt which my mother sew in money and a switch knife . if ever anybody try to attack I , I should use it . whoever hear that ; you will be in rag , hairless , nameless , sometimes walk naked because there be no clothes for I . we be take into a big barrack . you do not know who be there and there be about 1,000 people in one barrack .", "Anthony : just a prisoner in a uniform ? Lily : no , no . the first thing that they strip the professional , jewish people from they profession . they be just treat like dirt , like laborer , like slave . they be strip away from they human dignity .", "the first thing that they strip the professional , jewish people from they profession . they be just treat like dirt , like laborer , like slave . they be strip away from they human dignity . this be the first thing , be to break they spirit . Anthony : so after he leave the ghetto , he be no longer a pharmacist ?", "a : much later , much later . shortly before they take we away to the work camp . so anyway , the kapo say they be go to come and select we , they need 250 girl for the work camp and they take you to a different area , different camp , a different area and again they shower we , oh God , again , naked and disinfect you . a man have to disinfect you , prisoner , and we be shy , so shy and so ashamed for the man to disinfect you , with the hose , you know . Q : do you remember when this be ?", "so I do not know if they say the truth or not . and another thing I have to say -- when we go to the work camp , I have this very good friend of mine from my home town -- Rochela . and they choose we naked to go to the work camp . so she be very skinny and she be right behind I and I go forward -- they let -- they point I to go forward , I go forward and I be there and I be look for my friend Rochela and she be not there . I give a look to the other side and she be over there -- purple and blue and that be the last that I see of she .", "you could not have a pimple on you body and here they give you for six month not to get you period and we break out in all kind of boil and as a matter of fact , , I do have a boil on my belly but the ss man do not see I , he must have be distract so he do not see the boil , he just point I to go ahead . but we all have something from that -- it be not normal and that be the last I see Rochela . so they choose you naked -- you could not be too skinny , you could not be too fat . you could not have a boil , you could not ... ... can you imagine ? Q : you could not be sick ?", "it be a horrible stench . Q : when you go to the camp , you be separate and where do you go ? a : the first time , the first thing I notice we be strip of all clothing , all belongings . next thing I get a number tattoo . Q : that be do right away ?", "for example , there be one -- well I will tell you about that one because it almost cause we death . also the reason she call my mother into another room be because this lady also make doll which be fully clothe adult doll but they be apparently anatomically correct . so she show this lovely doll but then invite my mother into this next room so that she could undress this male doll and show my mother that it have all its anatomical part . well , while my mother and this lady be out of the room I turn and look at the wall behind I on which hang a picture that this woman have also make . the picture be of a sort of cottage and a yard fill with chicken and there be flower against the cottage and there be little window with shutter and a door and so forth .", "the people who arrive in the transport , they see these big move van with the chimney . and the ss do not threaten they , they be very nice , they say you know we bring you to we farm , because they have be tell that if you be nice to people they will listen to you . and they be there to undress and they say we be go out to a thing and by the time they get there they be already dead . September 1 , 1943 , the ghetto , we german ghetto be completely surround by ss during the night . Q : so we be talk , be there still a division between russian and german jew at this point ?", "everybody go as a gardener . the gardener we never see again . but we be push on the side and we go to a barrack and we have to undress . we have still not prison uniform but we have old clothes mark with ___ . so we have to undress .", "but we be push on the side and we go to a barrack and we have to undress . we have still not prison uniform but we have old clothes mark with ___ . so we have to undress . the little thing we have , here , here , here . nothing .", "the german kapo hate we . the polish kapo , you know . and we be put , just to give you a example , where to undress , this be high in the mountain , we have to undress , we have to run into a shower and this be originally the gas chamber , and the kapo say that be it . and we do not know what would happen . Q : the kapo say you would die ?", "Q : he family ? a : yeah . so before they go into the train , they undress the people . because they know that everybody have hide something in the clothing , which be true . the same thing with I .", "Q : you explain you boy 's collar . a : I sew it in . so everybody who go into the train , woman , man , child , undress . naked to the train . the train , they be roll to Treblinka .", "a : I sew it in . so everybody who go into the train , woman , man , child , undress . naked to the train . the train , they be roll to Treblinka . you know when you come to Treblinka , that be it .", "it be not the shop anymore . Q : you first rude shock ? a : yeah , when we be count and everything , we go into a room to undress and to shave . barber that shave the head and they start give we the striped suit . Q : the striped suit .", "we go to Germany and they stop in a place , and they unlouse we , you know . be cold already . everybody have to undress and be a few barrel with soap . Q : chemical ? a : with a brush .", "Q : chemical ? a : with a brush . you naked . you go to this veld . the guy with the brush clean you up .", "then they catch the three , the two brother and the sister , ____ and _____ . then the two brother , they go first . everybody get 25 or 35 on the naked ___ . Q : in the buttock ? a : and the ss be strongest ss .", "then the german people be there ; they realize that there be a girl with a orthopedic shoe . so one leg be shorter than the other . they take and they realize when she be naked . they take the naked girl out and take she away , naked as she be , because of the foot . now , I know , later I know that she be take to the other room to be kill .", "so one leg be shorter than the other . they take and they realize when she be naked . they take the naked girl out and take she away , naked as she be , because of the foot . now , I know , later I know that she be take to the other room to be kill . because they realize that only when she be naked .", "they take the naked girl out and take she away , naked as she be , because of the foot . now , I know , later I know that she be take to the other room to be kill . because they realize that only when she be naked . Q : do you know this girl ? a : no , no .", "at that time , I do not understand , of course , what be happen . but I have the whole picture in my eye . she be take naked and kill . Q : she be , how old ? a : eighteen .", "then we know already what be happen . the big head of the ______ , when the selection be , the big truck come to the lager and people be just , be black . for instance , after a selection for which they make , nude , _______ the naked people be just throw on the platform of this van and take away . these child be just throw on this platform and take away . they collect the child , put in this and that be my twentieth birthday .", "there be french car , cattle car and they be make out of heavy tin . the heat without water ; sometimes they open the door , half of they be dead . they have to wait sometimes two , three day till there be place to process they in , to take they down to undress and to gas they and then later to cremate they . well , actually in the beginning , they be not cremate . there be ditch which they fill the ditch , this be near the russian border , so there be ditch make , anti-tank ditch .", "there be no bloodshed or anything . they just come in . in the very begin , I do not know if it be the same day they march in or the next day , all the Jews , right away they zero in on the Jews , we have to meet at the marketplace and right away they start with they decree to strip we of all material possession slowly but very systematically . the first request be for the Jews to give all the gold , maybe all the silver , all the radio , everything that have any material value , carpet , Persian carpet , you would not imagine , fur , fur coat , all sort of thing we have to bring to the marketplace , or whatever , I think it be the marketplace , the Germans take that . and that go on for about a week .", "rabbis to donate to commandateur , the commanding officer of the garrison of Minsk Mazowiecki about one kilogram of gold every two month or every three month I can not tell . but we know that they be force because jewish friend tell we that they have to donate all gold . once they strip they with entire possession , then they kill they . Q : do you see this massacre ? a : I see only after massacre when they be use remain jewish people to load the body on the track and take they away to some massive grave .", "when we arrive there nothing happen . we be in such a disarray and tired . the very next morning they tell we to undress . Q : where do they hold you overnight ? a : in one of the barracks -- get undressed , wash , and before we get cup of tea you might call .", "`` he do not know too much but what he do not know , he make up with he mouth . the first job be a elevator shaft that have to be repair . one of the gear be strip and we either have to buy another gear , which be not available because they quit make those . all of the factory be gear for production for the war . so , we have to improvise and put in two gear , tooth we call it .", "all of the factory be gear for production for the war . so , we have to improvise and put in two gear , tooth we call it . we have to take out those two that be strip and file they down and put in two in they place . since we do not have anything to weld it , we have to drill a hole into that gear and then set it up with some screw so it will work for the time be . then that other Karp come over and say , `` boy-oh-boy .", "do anything in particular come to mind when you think of these year ? a : yes , every day there be beat and kill and smash the prisoner , execution almost every day , every day a pill , yeah and they call the number go to work so what happen they take they outside the camp and execution , shoot they . and I think I remember by the end I be there they bring twelve thousand russian war prisoner to Auschwitz and as war prisoner , it be winter time , December , they be twenty four hour naked and a very cold night and snow even . then they put they into barracks and give they some kind of clothing but the food be very , very little so through the winter they almost all die out . there be only a few hundred left of those war prisoner .", "my father would point out to I and say these be refugee from Germany . also we see photograph in the newspaper , picture in the newspaper of the rioting . the story that be behind they ; where they be strip of german citizenship and the polish government declare quickly that they strip they also of the polish citizenship . so they be people without citizenship ; it be very sad ; it be a foretaste of thing to come to a unimaginable proportion and degree . Q : earlier we be talk about patriotism , the polish patriotism of you father .", "then on the platform , which on the right and a platform on the left which separate we from the other section of the train , there be big floodlight and there be guard that be stand on both side . be just maybe two or three guard . all of a sudden you hear the sound of a rolling door open and a man , strip down to he trunk , run out of this heat . he just run and the Germans , the german guard , they begin to hunt he like a rabbit . he say , Ich _______ , I have he !", "open-air latrine . we stand there for what seem a very long time . I believe we be eventually order to strip totally and in the nude march to a delousing showering facility , a cleaning facility . the guard would kick , if I recall correctly , these be Ukrainians that be on the inside of that concentration camp . ukrainian guard in black uniform would kick inmate and they habit be to kick inmate until they curl up on the ground or be too ill to respond .", "ukrainian guard in black uniform would kick inmate and they habit be to kick inmate until they curl up on the ground or be too ill to respond . I do not know how many people die under these kick outburst but I know that they injure many people in that process . when we arrive at the showering process and delousing as they would call it , we go through a room whereby we head be -- we be give a crew cut and the Germans or the ukrainian guard at that time would spit on we head to give they the ability to shave a stripe from front to back so it would wind up like a one to two inch stripe run through a otherwise crew cut , there would be a shave strip . I suppose that this be do so that we would not be able to escape . so in the Gross-Rosen camp , we receive this crew cut and a shave strip through the middle , run from front to back of the head .", "when we arrive at the showering process and delousing as they would call it , we go through a room whereby we head be -- we be give a crew cut and the Germans or the ukrainian guard at that time would spit on we head to give they the ability to shave a stripe from front to back so it would wind up like a one to two inch stripe run through a otherwise crew cut , there would be a shave strip . I suppose that this be do so that we would not be able to escape . so in the Gross-Rosen camp , we receive this crew cut and a shave strip through the middle , run from front to back of the head . the situation inside the Gross-Rosen camp , as I describe before , whenever there be a chance for the ukrainian guard to kick anyone , they enjoy that . I do not recall any killing or hanging inside that camp .", "I recall that Oskar Schindler just come out of jail not long before we come to Brunnlitz -lrb- Brnenec , Czech Republic -rrb- . when we already be in Brunnlitz , this Amon Goeth who conduct all these hanging and shooting and murderous act in Krakow Plaszow also appear in Brunnlitz . at one time , I remember see he but this Amon Goeth be no longer the Amon Goeth of the ss guard with the almighty power but somehow they strip he of all he rank while he be in jail . because he be in jail at that time , as rumor would have it , for steal the transport of food that would arrive into the concentration camp from some jewish organization abroad or Red Cross or something . that he be steal those and he be turn they into gold and diamond and other thing .", "Judge : and what happen to you ? tell we what happen to you . Lou : we be march on top of a huge pile of clothing , and we be old to undress . and we inquire , `` what happen to the people who once wear this clothing ? '' we be tell they go through the chimney .", "so -- I do not know about wa -- oh , when we arrive , I like to go back there . we go in stripe uniform or what -- I do not know how to call it , man take we over . then we go for awhile , and ja -- and polish woman take we over , and I be tell get the -- undress , everybody . and the man be walk around we , you know ? they do not pay any attention to we anyway .", "finally there be not too many . I mean , relatively too much . but we have just hear of what the lageralteste tell we , we see the dead people , and to one side -- we be stand outside , a big van pass by with ma -- with naked body , dead body . very shock . Q : be there people -- be there woman who die in -- in you barracks , in you area , on a regular basis ?", "you could come for seven day . so , you get seven coupon . it be one coupon and you cut off seven strip . at one point , they try to do it for two week , and then somebody else get a turn . how it be decide , administer , as to who get they , or which factory -- that be do behind closed door , I do not know , but there be a lot of protection involve .", "a : no , I do not have a sense . I have never hear of such a thing , and it do not -- it do not really fall into place . Q : but , he tell you he take child into a room and undress they . a : yeah , or molest they . Q : or molest they in some way .", "he come back in subsequent week and month and it be a matter of molestation . the man be impotent , but he do not like to know that or hear about it , and to I it be utterly frightening because at one point I be not even quite sure how you become pregnant until Luba tell I . Q : do he undress you ? a : no . Q : so , he do not -", "a : yes , it be sew the metal frame that go around a shovel that a soldier carry on he belt to dig a trench , and those be sew on a goat or a causa -lrb- ph -rrb- , as you say in a yiddish . that mean you sit on a bench and in front of you be like a head with a vice , with a wooden vice , and you put the leather into -- the two piece of leather into the wooden vice , you have a awl to punch the whole , and then you have a long string with two needle , one right , one leave -- and you sew a double stitch like this , and it be piecework . I mean , they count it , and once in a while , there be ten strip to a unit . once in awhile , we be a strip short , and then you have to go to the foreman , who be a young man we age and you have to do a lot of explain and a lot of excuse , and then you would get another strip , but they be count out carefully because the Germans have ship they carefully . the reason my strip disappear be I steal they .", "that mean you sit on a bench and in front of you be like a head with a vice , with a wooden vice , and you put the leather into -- the two piece of leather into the wooden vice , you have a awl to punch the whole , and then you have a long string with two needle , one right , one leave -- and you sew a double stitch like this , and it be piecework . I mean , they count it , and once in a while , there be ten strip to a unit . once in awhile , we be a strip short , and then you have to go to the foreman , who be a young man we age and you have to do a lot of explain and a lot of excuse , and then you would get another strip , but they be count out carefully because the Germans have ship they carefully . the reason my strip disappear be I steal they . I steal six strip because my shoe have no sole , and I put they in the top of my boot , and I walk through the inspection ; it be like at the airport .", "I mean , they count it , and once in a while , there be ten strip to a unit . once in awhile , we be a strip short , and then you have to go to the foreman , who be a young man we age and you have to do a lot of explain and a lot of excuse , and then you would get another strip , but they be count out carefully because the Germans have ship they carefully . the reason my strip disappear be I steal they . I steal six strip because my shoe have no sole , and I put they in the top of my boot , and I walk through the inspection ; it be like at the airport . they would tap you from neck to the bottom .", "once in awhile , we be a strip short , and then you have to go to the foreman , who be a young man we age and you have to do a lot of explain and a lot of excuse , and then you would get another strip , but they be count out carefully because the Germans have ship they carefully . the reason my strip disappear be I steal they . I steal six strip because my shoe have no sole , and I put they in the top of my boot , and I walk through the inspection ; it be like at the airport . they would tap you from neck to the bottom . occasionally you have to undress , and I only tell about it after I have all six out .", "I steal six strip because my shoe have no sole , and I put they in the top of my boot , and I walk through the inspection ; it be like at the airport . they would tap you from neck to the bottom . occasionally you have to undress , and I only tell about it after I have all six out . nobody know , and people think I must have lose my mind , but I have no sole for the winter . Q : and , then you get somebody to fix they .", "nobody know , and people think I must have lose my mind , but I have no sole for the winter . Q : and , then you get somebody to fix they . a : I get a shoemaker to sole the shoe , and the reason he do not talk be because he could keep half of the strip , and he could sell they for bread . I think it be about the only time I steal . that be why I never buy a pair of boot , never .", "the side be sort of stiff , and -- but they only last one winter or maybe a winter and a half and I come through the sole , and I have frostbite , and they be pull up boot in sort of a nice brown leather , but much too soft for shoe . they be for a hatbox , not for shoe . but I have enough room below the knee to get a thin item into it like a strip of leather , and those I steal . Q : so , why be that you have never buy a pair of boot since then ? a : because I remember those boot .", "and there be a woman who recognize a mother who have be there a while , and she bring extra food , but that be already the next day . from there , they march we those that be fit-looking or not elderly or not child anymore , into a barracks . we be ask to undress , drop all jewelry , fold the clothing neatly , and then they take we to another barracks and they shave we hair , and Dr. Singer 's daughter ask , `` could not we rather have a number ? '' and , the answer be , `` here you take what you get . you do not ask for anything . ''", "she might have be from Romania . I do not know . she do not come with we , though she tell we after a couple of week that there would be a inspection , to undress , take off the rag . there would be a ss inspection team in the center of the count area . we should put the dress over the right arm , and walk pass the three ss man as fast as possible , and one of they motion with a stick or a ride whip , a leather whip , right left , right left .", "so when we get all undressed they keep we for hour , they have we wait for hour on the street . tape # 2 , side 1 -rrb- -rrb- so when you get there and you have to take all you clothes off , what happen ? and they have we wait for hour and hour on the street naked , and those ss man walk around among we , and then they take we in and they separate we . who separate ? the ss .", "Yeh , that be on the next day . where do you sleep on the first day ? by the time they get we off the train , Marilyn , it do not go so fast , by the time they organize we in one place and get we to undress , and then they haul we all into one big barrack , and everyone get shave off the hair , shave off like Dad standing and shaving ; my head wa ... and then they take we into shower , and then we come out and then it be already late in the night , by the time they get we into a barrack and they show you be you bunk bed be go to be , so Manya and I climb up to one , and Hela Shgivatch , and the next morning when we get out 5 o'clock in the morning we get out , `` appel platz '' to be count , by every barrack they get they people out to be count . we get so hysterical when we look at each other the first time without hair , you know . when they get we back , it be in the middle of the night , it be dark , nobody could see nobody , there be never light in the barracks , you could not undress or dress by light , whatever we have to dress or undress , so you could not see what you look , but when it start to get in the morning a little light , daylight would set in .", "by the time they get we off the train , Marilyn , it do not go so fast , by the time they organize we in one place and get we to undress , and then they haul we all into one big barrack , and everyone get shave off the hair , shave off like Dad standing and shaving ; my head wa ... and then they take we into shower , and then we come out and then it be already late in the night , by the time they get we into a barrack and they show you be you bunk bed be go to be , so Manya and I climb up to one , and Hela Shgivatch , and the next morning when we get out 5 o'clock in the morning we get out , `` appel platz '' to be count , by every barrack they get they people out to be count . we get so hysterical when we look at each other the first time without hair , you know . when they get we back , it be in the middle of the night , it be dark , nobody could see nobody , there be never light in the barracks , you could not undress or dress by light , whatever we have to dress or undress , so you could not see what you look , but when it start to get in the morning a little light , daylight would set in . and we look at each other , there be , people get so hysterical , cry , and laughing and , scream . I just can not describe to you the feeling what be be then , we all look like you know what , like we father 's , you know when a girl 's head be shave off , she look just like she father , in Manya I see she father , Manya see in I my father .", "just from day to day , from hour to hour , believe I , you never know , and then they , one day , and then , almost every week , 2-3 time a week they make `` selectzia '' . what do you mean by that ? `` seleczia '' mean a selection of people , they have we all undress and Mengele , you hear about Mengele , the one that be be film now , would you believe that he clap I like this on my back , that bastard . one day , they assemble we all , naked , and Hela , Rusha 's sister , have two other girl at the Plaszow camp , we keep together , Manya and I , and we always try to keep Manya between Hela and I , Rusha 's sister and I , because Manya have scar , from operation , and if he see a scar , or a pimple on somebody , and you do not look good anymore , you go here ; you do not know where you be go , but we assume . so we try to keep Manya between we , but he say `` March , march '' , so when I come by he say to I `` die vet noch gut arbeit leissen '' that I will produce a lot of work yet , so we all go by and we be lucky , we could go and get dress again .", "what do you mean by that ? `` seleczia '' mean a selection of people , they have we all undress and Mengele , you hear about Mengele , the one that be be film now , would you believe that he clap I like this on my back , that bastard . one day , they assemble we all , naked , and Hela , Rusha 's sister , have two other girl at the Plaszow camp , we keep together , Manya and I , and we always try to keep Manya between Hela and I , Rusha 's sister and I , because Manya have scar , from operation , and if he see a scar , or a pimple on somebody , and you do not look good anymore , you go here ; you do not know where you be go , but we assume . so we try to keep Manya between we , but he say `` March , march '' , so when I come by he say to I `` die vet noch gut arbeit leissen '' that I will produce a lot of work yet , so we all go by and we be lucky , we could go and get dress again . but then , this , be this in April 1944 ?", "a : no . Q : No . so you be very careful how you dress and undress -- a : careful how I dress and undress and all that , and do not forget I -- we never -- we never base -lsb- indecipherable -rsb- always have this -- you know there be just a -- just you wash you -- th-the lower part of you body do not get much -- much sanitation as it be , you know . you just wash the upper body , the foot or leg and this and that , so -- so I never -- th-there -- there be no -- there be no shower , you know , and then --", "Q : No . so you be very careful how you dress and undress -- a : careful how I dress and undress and all that , and do not forget I -- we never -- we never base -lsb- indecipherable -rsb- always have this -- you know there be just a -- just you wash you -- th-the lower part of you body do not get much -- much sanitation as it be , you know . you just wash the upper body , the foot or leg and this and that , so -- so I never -- th-there -- there be no -- there be no shower , you know , and then -- Q : right , right .", "Q : right , right . a : -- or bath or anything like that . but -- but when I undress , sure , at night , dressi -- undress and dress , always -- because that be there , it be there , I -- I know , I be aware of it , and -- and there be no doubt about it , that -- Q : and nobody question you that you be do some -- you be dress and undress in a way -- a : not at all , no --", "a : -- or bath or anything like that . but -- but when I undress , sure , at night , dressi -- undress and dress , always -- because that be there , it be there , I -- I know , I be aware of it , and -- and there be no doubt about it , that -- Q : and nobody question you that you be do some -- you be dress and undress in a way -- a : not at all , no -- Q : No .", "I have a principle -- if somebody be stick it will be I , not the baby . and I get stick a few time , you know with the pin , but I will not stick he . but I take care of the baby and I get the milk back , too , that be such a lovely thing , when you baby get a bottle and all of a sudden this mess be all over you and the only thing you can do be make they comfortable and then you go to the bathroom and undress . that be all you can do . and we do everything together .", "there be no privacy . and if they think you do not wash yourself good enough they come with the big spray hose and spray ice cold water over you , midwinter , and it be cold . Q : people be naked , no clothes on ! a : no , you have to take everything off . it be in the morning .", "it be a special barrack with shower in they , and then you all go in there and you get a shower . it be pretty hot , nice and warm , and you get one towel for three people , and then let you dry outside . you go outside naked and you have to dry yourself -- if you be number three you get a wet towel . in the winter it be not too nice . but it be one of the thing to make you feel real small , to bring you down .", "I be not say that in the larger camp there be not a more systematic way for the german to kill off people , as much as they could . they have certain way to keep you always on you toe . since something could happen , once when we be in the arbeits-commando outside the camp , you know , and work in the forest or so , all of a sudden one day we come as one of these big ss officer come , we have to take all we clothes off -- we stand there , a couple of hundred people all naked -- and we have to dig a ditch . so we think right away : `` well , there we go ! '' for we know that it happen , that you have to dig a ditch and then they come with the machine gun , `` Brrrt ! ''", "for we know that it happen , that you have to dig a ditch and then they come with the machine gun , `` Brrrt ! '' and they all fall in the ditch , and they close the ditch and that be it . so , when we have to dig the ditch , stand there naked , and we think , `` well , that be the end of we . '' I never see so many people stand there and pray , hope that something would happen . and it really happen .", "Q : I read from someone who be in the camp and who say , '' how can you believe in the goodness of man , anymore . in the camp everyone fight against everybody else . '' what he be say be that the protection which society with its mores and law give each of we be strip away there , so you just have people , almost like animal , fight each other , at least more openly fight each other . and that after such a experience he could not believe in the goodness of man anymore . the truth about man be that man be a evil animal .", "how much worse it be every day , every day you get a spoon more of misery . Life in camp be really not show . show a bunch of dead people lay naked there in heap . well , that be a normal sight for we , I mean . at least 100 or 200 people on a heap , lay there wait to be cremate .", "a : that be a very good point . the french interned my family as be german citizen . although the Germans have strip they of they citizenship -lrb- by the Nuremberg law -rrb- , they have to be examine -lrb- before be free individually -rrb- . later on they be reintern and reexamine because the french want to make sure that they have no traitor , no foreign agent , in they midst . otherwise say : everyone of german birth , who do not have any other citizenship - specifically make sure that Americans , who do have US citizenship , even if they be bear in Germany , be not part of that .", "we drive to bingen through the Rhine Gorge . it be a gorge and that be what you call it in this country ; over there it be a `` valley . '' it be a fairly narrow strip which contain the Rhine river , which be by that time more than halfway down to the sea . the river be constrain to be only 90 foot wide so it flow rather rapidly . it be the area of the `` Mauseturm '' -lrb- the tower on a island where , the legend have it , mouse go to devour a wicked Bishop who have take refuge there from he flock -rrb- , the Niebelungen rock and the legend of the `` Lorelei '' -lrb- the maiden who sit on top of a rock and enchant the boatmen to forget about the rock and so he do drown in the river -rrb- .", "a : thing change naturally when the war break out , between Germany and France -lrb- that be September 30 , 1939 -rrb- in 1939 . Q : then what happen ? a : we have to report to the -lrb- `` we '' mean all the adult male 17 through 55 , then extend to the age of 60 , within the week , who either be german or have be german before they be strip of they citizenship by the Nuremberg law -rrb- stadium in Paris . the Stadium de Colomb , all the Germans and all the Austrians -lrb- Austria have be annex to Germany in 1938 -rrb- . there be no money to be bring with you .", "Q : what be you mother 's position ? a : yes , I listen to the tape -lrb- of the interview with Margaret Ebert -rrb- , but I do remember she while I be grow up . I do not remember she working in the law firm -lrb- obviously mean Paul Ebert 's law firm -rrb- where my father work , because he quit too early -lrb- after 1934 Jews be strip of they licens to practice law . Medicine etc. -rrb- and try to sell insurance . after that my mother work for the HIAS -lrb- Hebrew Immigrant Society -rrb- to try to get people out -lrb- of Germany -rrb- .", "and intentionally -- no absorption . they intentionally keep they out . what do the Egyptians , we ally now , the Egyptians -- what do they do with these camp in the Gaza Strip , with these refugee camp ? after Israel take over , let 's face it , I think they live with luxury compare with what they live now . of course , it be hard on they , but , for heaven 's sake , we have to stop sometimes .", "Q : but to bother to move you , use railroad stock to do it -lrb- when they need for railroad stock elsewhere and for military purpose be most urgent -rrb- and yet you be all die along the way . a : yes . the example be : when they undress we -- you know , take away the watch , the clothes , etc. , you have to have every piece of clothing in a separate container . it have to be precise . they have a bag for watch , they have a bag for tooth , they have a bag for glass , for ring , etc. .", "that be when we get there they must have just set up that camp because we first assignment be build barracks and we be later then assign . Q : when you get to this Buna what happen to you clothes ? a : we be tell to strip completely naked at the time . this be the eastern part of Germany and still very , very cold , and I remember we have to strip completely naked and run completely naked from one block , mean barrack to another barrack and there we be wait for some instruction or whatnot . I remember wait .", "Q : when you get to this Buna what happen to you clothes ? a : we be tell to strip completely naked at the time . this be the eastern part of Germany and still very , very cold , and I remember we have to strip completely naked and run completely naked from one block , mean barrack to another barrack and there we be wait for some instruction or whatnot . I remember wait . it be very , very cold .", "what we have see now slowly dawn on we , we be see murder in front of we eye and so that be the very first beginning , and then we be send to have we number tattoo . we be not call by name anymore we be only call by number . we hair be shave off completely and we be assign one thin striped suit and we be assign to certain block , mean that be where we belong and that be the early beginning , and then naturally when you be strip of all you dignity by realize you be non more name , there be only a number , by have you hair shave off and by be force to run naked around by not have the most natural rights in any manner , you notice right away that this be something out of the extraordinary . naturally you be confront with a situation which I suppose create a period in we life which at that time which at that time of complete despair or complete inability to cope with you own survival , and that be why during the very early period , I remember distinctly , many people in my block walk into a loaded wire because they psychologically could not cope with that first period that you be not a human being , that you be worse than a animal . they just could not cope with it and they be run every day i remember notice people hang on these laded wire , who just could not take it , and that be the very early part , the first few day of we be there .", "naturally you be confront with a situation which I suppose create a period in we life which at that time which at that time of complete despair or complete inability to cope with you own survival , and that be why during the very early period , I remember distinctly , many people in my block walk into a loaded wire because they psychologically could not cope with that first period that you be not a human being , that you be worse than a animal . they just could not cope with it and they be run every day i remember notice people hang on these laded wire , who just could not take it , and that be the very early part , the first few day of we be there . Q : when you first start see this , as you say , the murder , the strip of one dignity , how be you able little by little to cope ? a : good question . I have ask myself this many , many time .", "this type , these be the work shoe , and only the privileged , studen aldeste or kapo , block aldeste they be allow because they be the privileged type of people . they be allow , they get special permission from the ss to wear good shoe . they have a better type of a suit strip yes , but high class , they have they make by tailor from we own people who have be tailor , they get custom make while everyone else have to take what be give to they while walk through these section where they be assign , these privileged people include these I mention take off these shoe and give these people the normal type of shoe assign . Q : be there ever a chance , how do one become a block aldeste or a kapo or ... . .", "Q : but do they give they ? a : yes they do . somehow they have a way of , they could not strip we . we have to have some sort of bare necessity . but of course the thing that happen , while we be work with the construction we have to insulate -lrb- word miss in original transcript -rrb- , and they give you something like I would call it today fiberglass , and one of we stupid girl say I have a idea , it be cotton wool and she use it for she period .", "a : you have no idea . I mean I be in Auschwitz and I see the buring and I could not grab the idea . it be three day when I be in Auschwitz and I see naked people walk towards the gas chamber . I think I be dream -- I just could not grab it . and they come in -- people -- be the ss come in I do not know and they look at we number and you know I have a number there and I probably be like in a dream -- I mean I could not grad this whole thing what be go on there -- and after they be out , I ask why do they look at the number ?", "and then one day , ja , everyday , for instance , when we come there , we have already everyday a shower , a sauna . a sauna be call -- it be a big place and there be just one shower next to the other and everybody get undressed and take they shower and then we be stand a little bit until we dry up and then we put everything on again . one day we be stand there , it be after I be there a short time , naked , stark naked we be stand there and the leiter form the camp come in - you know he be in court , it be in the paper he be put to death -- he name be Hessler . and at this time he be plead he be so good to the girl and nobody say a good word for he . he be put to death .", "he be put to death . I wish I could have go -- I would have tell they all the goodness he do in the camp . we be stand there all naked and he come in . I mean he could not have wait until we be dress ? I mean we be stark naked , he walk in , all the soldier walk in -- you just be not a human be anymore .", "we be stand there all naked and he come in . I mean he could not have wait until we be dress ? I mean we be stark naked , he walk in , all the soldier walk in -- you just be not a human be anymore . okay , I manage to stand in the back but people have to stand in the front too . and he be stand there and hold a speech -- there be a munitions factory there and he say up to now , no jew ever work there because we be not trustworthy .", "so he give we the charcoal . you know here and there , there be still a few german and you know what two girl do . they take two well dress german woman and they undress they in the street . Q : I want to ask you , you must have come in contact with german during those first few day and week . how do you feel towards they ?", "we not ask anything -- we be just ask to eat because we be hungry . Q : where there any instance of violence against the Germans ? a : no , just that they undress they but you know the Americans they behave unbelievable . one night we go and this cook we have with we -- she say would you like good chicken soup -- that be so cute . so you know what she do -- there be a peasant living there and some chicken run around .", "Q. Men and woman together ? a. Sure . we never undress completely . you would be surprised how good you can sleep without change clothes and very often , I notice that I go to bed with my shoe still on . Q .", "I be carry that and they be debate about it -- they finally throw it on the floor and it go into a million piece and I just put the case into my pocket . anyway , I miss the train and I have to wait in Aachen for a few hour and in the meantime whenever one of these ss guy come around I get a slap in the face , or something like this , you know , real hero . and then I have to undress and they look up into the , you know , all place . by the way , I have a wonderful revenge . the first city , as a american gi , that we occupy in Germany be Aachen , the same place , and we have take a entire bunch of 200 of the border ss that we have take prisoner and who be in one compound .", "it be sort of a sweet revenge . they be very embarrassed . it be the middle of the winter and they have to undress in the courtyard and look up each other ' rectum and thing like that which they have do to I and so on . Q : as a sixteen year old boy travel alone I be sure you be quite frightened . g : well , I be amazingly ... I admire myself in a sense afterwards because I be amazingly compose there .", "and probably in pretty good shape , compare to some of the other . Q : and then you say you be put back into row , and then what happen ? a : then we be march into another part of the camp and take to a barracks where we have to undress and throw away all belongings except we shoe and a belt , I remember . and we be chase through a cold shower . by that time it must have be around midnight and we stand shiver in the night air there until we be dry and formed line in row of five .", "-lrb- laugh -rrb- we could not be mistake for anybody else . we be , by that time , walk skeleton . we have we hair shear , and only one strip of hair in the center . we have these blue and while striped uniform . and we be guard by heavily armed ss as if we would be the most precious possession that the world would have to offer .", "we do not know anything about Auschwitz . and about a month after they be send out , a packet come to my aunt from Auschwitz of she husband 's clothing follow by a telegram that he have die in Auschwitz . and when she look at the clothing , she could not believe it , because my uncle evidently use to undress with the shirt and the undershirt take off at the same time . and the shirt and the undershirt be take off at the same time . we do not know about Auschwitz , or what they be do to people in Auschwitz , so we assume that the telegram be a fake .", "it be a de-licing process . we get there the beginning of April , I think . we have to sit naked outside , leave everything except we shoe and belt . and go into the shower . come out from the shower and dunk the shoe and the belt in a certain solution .", "but they do not cut like this , because they want a opening on the Mediterranean . so it cut like this , and so the whole part of Bordeaux , the whole southwest of France be in . Q : you be close to the Mediterranean , but the Germans want to have a strip along the Mediterranean . a : no , we be parallel to the Atlantic . the Atlantic be here .", "they be put in freight train , and each of these freight `` wagon '' be completely close , and they pack the people in to the point that it be usually could be twenty people , let 's say twenty soldier , would be in , but this time they put hundred people , old , young , without any water , and they lock it and the train eventually go to somewhere . when this be describe , the circumstance , it become very obvious to I and to all of we that the future of those people be very gloomy , and this be something much more serious than a matter of take away this , or take away that , from certain people . it be a matter of life-threatening situation , and they , of course , be completely strip of they whole property . from there on , then , I have personally no , whatsoever , expectation from the Germans except to be kill . Q : then until 1944 , until the german invasion , you have mobilization , there be a hungarian army , that be fight ...", "we know about the digging , too , because the word get to we before it even start , but as they tell we , that be go to be for keep potato for the winter -lrb- laugh -rrb- so , I know exactly where it happen . and then when I read the book it describe exactly what they do . they tell they to undress . and they kill they one on top of the other . that be what they do .", "instead of the Nazis allow proper distribution of food , they want to see those people , like mad dog , how they be scramble . you know , when people be hungry , they kill each other for a slice of bread . so most of the people kill on that particular section -- on that strip -- they be fight to get that small bread . we come to Mauthausen , and supposedly we be suppose to get out . and we hear -- all , everything be a rumor mill -- we will not be allow to get out because there be no room leave , because there be many camp , from other place in Poland that they come here before we , and they fill up the camp .", "I guess I can not talk too much about it . my mother be bear of five child ; and nobody make it . when I think she have to be with allt hese strange people , naked ... Q : do they make all of you take you clothes off ? a : yes .", "one guy from we city be Cholmo . be a big , big guy . and Goett come with two dog , big dog , and he tell he to undress himself . everybody be watch . and he give the order to the two dog -- they tear he apart !", "and then they would take the ash out and put they into urn and sell they to they family or relative and so on , in any kind of way . that image of those furnace , of that kind of building , still haunt I to this day . he also tell we about the laundry of the building , and how they strip body and put they in there . and this be the picture that be to be replicate and duplicated , that we see in the other place that be liberate just within a short time after that . well , I have my driver with I - we company be white officer and black enlist man , who have also , of course , be deprive a bit - and one of the reason why I think we have a good guide be that my driver , who be black , be probably one of the first black to have a tour here of Buchenwald .", "and I recall during April of 1970 , after the intrusion into Cambodia and a few other event that happen in the ` 70s , I still recall some graduate student all exercise and upset over the military , and that it be go to widen the war in Viet Nam , and the chinese and Russians be go to come in by all of we activity and I say , `` no . '' and I recall tell some rabid , very active group here that I be more concerned about what be happen in Egypt . they be pooh-pooh , over whether the russian mig be buzz the israeli plane on the Gaza strip , and they be ready to take over , until we get word to the egyptian government about what the Russians be do , and they kick they out . but that save the Middle East . otherwise , the Russians be ready to take over .", "after my father and brother be take away from we , my mother and sister stay together . it be a very traumatic checking-in process . we have to undress . we come to a building where we have to proceed , let 's say , like from one room to the next . I have some slide of it I use when I present something on World War II or on camp -- a reel of slide that we family take in 1974 when we be in Germany .", "in the middle be a table , and there be a ss man in a white coat . we come in batch of several woman . we have to take we clothes off before we go in , and we be totally naked . my mother and sister , of course , we hold on together . I can not even describe now the feeling , how you feel in a situation like this .", "throw out every book . they be such idiot , you know . they would see naked figure , and they say , `` those dirty schwein jew . '' there be a Michelangelo . Q : where be this ?", "be you still in Hamburg ? a : Hamburg . they see Michelangelos and they would say , `` that dirty jew have naked figure . '' so it be just ridiculous . but they throw everything out .", "I be get angry when people tell I , `` all the Jews just go '' like sheep to the slaughter '' that be not true ! yes , some do , and they could not do anything else ! I would like to know what people would do if you be strip naked with dog on you . what else can you do ! in fact , I be tell that one of my uncle , be one of the leader , and he go in with the sh ' ma Yisroel -- somebody who have see it tell I that .", "they try to cross . if they do not quite make it , the spanish bullet hit they and they die . we find a naked man in the bush when he make it . the world be crazy . I tell you that .", "this have nothing to do with religion , nothing to do because you be afraid . this have to do with they get gun and machine gun , and a lot of army . you stand naked ! Q : and what do you teach you child about power ? about this act of survival ?", "half-burned body be still in the oven where they have be leave as the Germans flee . beside the oven be the emaciated body of prisoner they have not have time to burn . they be naked , stack like cordwood as you would you fireplace wood . further down be slat-sided cart that be also fill with body . these cart be use to bring the body from the gas chamber .", "I think , `` I be in a jungle between white people . '' that be how the people look to I . woman , girl , almost naked , shave completely . and the face from the sun . it must have be there so hot , or I do not know .", "I could not bend down and give it to they , because we be forbid to talk to they and we pass very quickly , but as unobtrusively as I could , I throw away two loaf of bread I have . then we walk into a bath installation . we be tell to undress completely and line up and give up we jewelry . I have a watch and I have a very lovely small diamond ring , my mother 's engagement ring . I do not want to give it to the ss .", "fortunately cold water come out . then we stand shiver , in another room . they leave we alone , and after several hour they issue either strip uniform or a ragged , very tear piece of civilian clothing . then we be tell to line up , and we march for several mile again to another part of the camp -- into barracks number 20 , I recall -- and we be seat , pack like sardine , in fives . we be seat with we leg cross .", "they would stand up when they search they , and they hold that thing in they hand like this . up there . they would search they all over but the thing they be look for -- they be really look for food -- they have a list and if they have jewelry on it , they would have strip they . but they be look , really for food , because people get really inventive . they use to take a salami and put it right in front and close to the jacket , or a loaf of bread .", "since we be there -- the Jews -- they think we should get the shot , too . but they want to show the difference between the Germans and the Jews , so they get two shot , we get one shot . -lrb- laughter -rrb- we all have to strip to the waist . I have from my wife a man 's ring , a wide one , and she have make two ring out of it . I be the only guy who be engage to a wife where the wife buy he the ring .", "I make myself a little cover and I wear it around my neck on a chain under my shirt , so nobody know about it , because we be not allow to have it . you get so use to it , you do not pay attention to it anymore . and the guy go up there and they say , `` Strip you shirt off . '' I take off the shirt , and this young ss doctor in he 30s give we the shot . and he come up to I , he say , `` what have you get there ? ''", "Q : can you remember any of the book and film that you have read or see that you think be worthwhile ? a : I and my wife have a book there which be from Latvia , take from german picture of Europe . they be show scene in Latvia where the Germans actually take picture where the woman be stand at the grave naked . and you may have see those picture someplace . this book be print by the Russians !", "do you know what you be here for ? '' and they be quite open about it . but the order keep be shout very quickly , `` Ger undress ! line up here ! line up there ! ''", "there be lot of people . two huge trench be dig out , as I see with my own eye . and they put layer and layer of dead body , they have to be undressed -- man and woman , it do not make any difference -- they undress they . they fill up the bottom of the trench . they pour calcium on top of it .", "a : that be the extermination barracks . about two or three week later , I happen to be fortunate to meet Dr. Mengele who be overlook this last transfer where I belong if there be anyone strong enough to be send out . that be the so-called selection where I be stand naked with many hundred other raise my left arm . we have to raise we left arm because that be show whether we rib show under the skin . if we be too thin there be no point in send we out and give we a piece of bread and take we to force labor because we could not stand it .", "if we be too thin there be no point in send we out and give we a piece of bread and take we to force labor because we could not stand it . I be select and in about two more week I be send with many other this time already with a dress and a coat and shoe . Q : during the selection you be naked ? a : yes , we have just one sheet of clothes which be throw at we and we have to put it on and whatever shoe you could find because shoe be very important if you have a infection on you foot , you be go to the gas chamber . Q : and all the other people who be in this barracks be exterminate ?", "they pick out 60 people from this group , I be among they , and they take we to the Camp . and while we be walk away from the other we hear they shoot all the rest . be not that terrible -- and they have they take off all the clothes , naked , and shoot they all . I be save . my brother be already there , and my mother , too .", "that be what you ask I . every one whom they select have to walk in the middle of the room with a platform like this . and like martyr they have to walk naked . and , eh , again , ah , ah , either leave or right , either she stay , or she have to go on this side . at that time we know already she go to the gas .", "and then they order we for work . I do not finish with the selection . the girl be naked , you mention . five ss and they have to parade to and fro and if she be too thin , she , if she have something on like this , I have now , she go to the gas chamber . Q : it be very humiliating .", "there be girl with typhus , they be on the carriage , and they be shoot in front of we , all of they -- thirty . then there be hut where the girl who be carrier of typhus ... they have typhus but they do not know it , but they be carry the bug . so they be separate too , naked of course . they be shoot in front of we . then we start to walk , it be marsh .", "it be so -- so -- every german , I think , be a -- think of a sadist because that be the nature of they . when we come to Auschwitz , as I say to you , we have to go to the road and they cut off we hair . I get such hysterical -- ah -- laugh -- laugh cramp that I start to rub and I see my friend -- they look -- like -lrb- word miss in original transcript -rrb- , I start through the shower , the Germans be stand there naked -- I have to rush through the shower , you know . such thing , unbelievable . or they take all we -- we dress and they throw we .", "because from Auschwitz you be send to different camp . Q : who provide you with thing like clothing ? a : Clothing come from Dachau you know the strip , the strip suit . Came from Dachau to Auschwitz . Q : Stripped , striped suit like prison suit ?", "Q : Stripped , striped suit like prison suit ? a : Yah . they come from you know and then you get it of course , you know , one shirt which be full of lice , you know , there be always the lice but you know you get a strip suit . you be always to wear a strip suit . Q : so if you run away you would easily be identify by the striped suit ?", "a : Yah . they come from you know and then you get it of course , you know , one shirt which be full of lice , you know , there be always the lice but you know you get a strip suit . you be always to wear a strip suit . Q : so if you run away you would easily be identify by the striped suit ? a : no , you could not run away .", "we little upholstery of fat under the skin . you become very emaciated . what I do not say earlier be that first thing that happen , of course , be you be strip of all you civilian clothes . you be shave from head to toe and that you be deal some prisoner clothes , striped , synthetic or cotton suit , no underwear , rarely sock and wooden shoe . that be you uniform .", "behind the road be about 12 or something people what they catch . between they be one jewish woman with a young child . they have to undress , nude . they have already the grave already . and they have to line up in front of the grave and they shoot one after the other .", "and matter of fact , they tell we Himmler come a few time around to look how it be build . so , I get in and we be ... first two day we do not do nothing . just ... first of all we have to undress , nude . and go through entlausung ... that be lice ... to clean ... Q : delousing .", "a : delousing , yeah . and shave the head . they shave we head , and then they give we strip suit . and they give we barracks , where to stay . then come around .", "you be lucky to have a pair of shoe . you be lucky nobody steal you shirt . it be some day when we do not work , you walk around almost naked . you use to wash what you have , dry it up and put it on again . that be the procedure .", "when I come in it be still judenlager -lrb- jewish camp -rrb- but then end of , I think 1942 , it become concentration camp . they give we ... we change from the civilian we have only the mark , no hair , and the yellow star . and then they switch it over ... it be such a bitter cold ... in the winter ... we be stand outside naked and they give we just a jacket and a pair of pants and some kind of shoe and nothing else . it be bitter cold . you almost freeze to death .", "he would walk we down to the first , the first building where I do not remember . I remember walk in and there be , uh , a very large room . we be tell to undress . yeah . we be tell to undress .", "we be tell to undress . yeah . we be tell to undress . I pull my precious little thing I have knit so many nice sweater and I be always keep they in a neat place . we be folding they up and put they in a neat pile against the wall .", "that be one of my better possession -lrb- laugh -rrb- . my hair , it be long and very . Q : and how dehumanizing , to be make to undress . a : that be a moment when you really feel it . yes .", "it be in , even in you short hair . it would even get into that . so we be naked and this man be , uh , operate this whole , shower -lrb- laugh -rrb- business . and we be not . we be not give any towel to dry off .", "only I have a couple high boot . they leave I that . along when we be stand naked , along come a man , he have - barbe . I : a band ? r : a band with the name `` Barbe . ''", "r : Yah . and then they come to Auschwitz . take a bath in january , naked cold . I do not know how people could overlive that point already . stand in the hallway , draft , naked , wet ...", "take a bath in january , naked cold . I do not know how people could overlive that point already . stand in the hallway , draft , naked , wet ... I : in the wintertime ? r : in January .", "it just -- when be my future , where be , where be I go ? nothing , that just go too . so , now you be just , ah , like a , a little animal , and , ah , they kind of , they kind of wait around and -- un a big hole to be examine again -- we be go in front of -- and there be line -- naked -- and we be go to the doctor , you know , we be go to be examine . what work we should we do in there ? who be suit for , for kind of work ?", "what work we should we do in there ? who be suit for , for kind of work ? so , we go through that -- well , we to the hole -- we go to the doctor , they say ... you be naked , you stand at this one -- be naked -- it kind of embarrassed -- and , ah , ah , I faint . I just collapse . there be no food .", "it be not the practice , apparently , to cremate every day . a concrete building be use as a temporary rest place . here the body be strip and pile up like cordwood . it seem incomprehensible , but 40 body be there , stone dead , stack four high and sprinkle with lime . all be similar to the body previously describe .", "Q : with the board ... a : Yah , with the board . it really ... it be a piece of wood ... a strip of wood ... you know , like this ... Q : yes . a : Yah , and it be a strip of wood , so you could not see it , and you could open this up , and they be sleep in that .", "it really ... it be a piece of wood ... a strip of wood ... you know , like this ... Q : yes . a : Yah , and it be a strip of wood , so you could not see it , and you could open this up , and they be sleep in that . they have the mattress in it and they be sleep during the night . Q : in other word , you be able to open that panel , and there be a mattress behind it , and that be where they sleep during the night .", "we give they the best medical treatment we possibly could , we have call in hospital unit there and they get the best that could be get . let I tell you a little bit how , let I expand upon what happen to the people after they be separate into these unit . the old and inform , people they could not use for anything be tell to undress that they clothes would be send some place to a delousing station . they undress , they be give a bar of soap and a towel . they be then take into a large building , clean as it could pos